WEBVTT

00:03.371 --> 00:05.537
(QUIET, TENSE MUSIC)

00:06.474 --> 00:14.213
¶¶¶

00:18.219 --> 00:20.486
JULIANNA CALLAGHAN,

00:20.488 --> 00:23.489
I VOW TO BE TRUE ALWAYS,

00:23.491 --> 00:26.592
TO GIVE YOU ALL OF MYSELF -
NO SECRETS -

00:27.361 --> 00:30.496
UNTIL DEATH PARTS US,
AND EVEN AFTER...

00:32.033 --> 00:33.599
'CAUSE I'VE BEEN YOURS

00:33.601 --> 00:35.234
SINCE THE FIRST DAY
I SAW YOU

00:35.236 --> 00:37.169
AND MADE A FOOL OF MYSELF.

00:37.171 --> 00:38.370
(GIGGLES)

00:38.372 --> 00:40.506
<i> 'CAUSE I KNEW RIGHT AWAY,</i>

00:40.508 --> 00:43.609
I KNEW THAT IT WAS YOU
OR NO ONE...

00:46.047 --> 00:47.212
EVEN THOUGH
YOU DIDN'T KNOW IT YET,

00:47.214 --> 00:49.314
AND I HAD TO BE PATIENT.

00:49.316 --> 00:50.549
I WAS RIGHT.
JUST SAYING.

00:50.551 --> 00:52.618
(GUESTS CHUCKLE)

00:59.326 --> 01:01.260
SAMUEL BRADDOCK,

01:03.197 --> 01:05.330
I VOW TO ALWAYS BE YOURS.

01:06.267 --> 01:08.834
(VOICE CATCHES,
SIGHS HAPPILY)

01:16.310 --> 01:20.079
I TRIED TO...
THINK OF WORDS,

01:21.182 --> 01:23.315
BUT THERE'S SO MANY...

01:23.317 --> 01:25.384
THERE'S SO MANY WORDS.

01:26.487 --> 01:30.322
SO, I VOW, TO YOU,
THIS...

01:32.426 --> 01:34.226
<i> (GUESTS LAUGH AND APPLAUD)</i>

01:34.228 --> 01:35.294
YEAH!

01:36.363 --> 01:37.429
(CHEERING)

01:41.368 --> 01:44.470
SO UM... SINCE YOU GUYS
ARE ALL HERE,

01:44.472 --> 01:45.804
<i> WE WOULD HAVE</i>
<i> TOLD YOU EARLIER,</i>

01:45.806 --> 01:48.373
<i> BUT WE DIDN'T WANT</i>
<i> TO JINX ANYTHING. </i>

01:48.375 --> 01:49.508
WE'RE THREE MONTHS
ALONG;

01:51.112 --> 01:52.678
WE'RE HAVING A BABY.

01:52.680 --> 01:55.814
(GUESTS GASP IN DELIGHT
AND APPLAUD)

02:01.322 --> 02:02.288
CONGRATULATIONS.
GOOD FOR YOU.
THANK YOU.

02:02.289 --> 02:03.255
ED: RIGHT ON!
SPIKE: COME HERE, YOU!

02:24.512 --> 02:25.844
(SWITCHES BEEP)

02:29.450 --> 02:31.450
(TOOLS THUNK IN TOOLKIT,
LID CLICKS SHUT)

02:31.452 --> 02:35.454
(PHONES RING,
ROOM BUZZES WITH CHATTER)

02:38.292 --> 02:39.892
911,
WHAT IS YOUR EMERGENCY?

02:40.828 --> 02:42.194
I'M WEARING A PEACH DRESS,

02:42.196 --> 02:43.495
SO IF YOU WEAR
A PEACH ROSE,

02:43.497 --> 02:45.264
IT MEANS... GRATITUDE.

02:46.367 --> 02:47.432
CLARK:
OH, RIGHT,
'CAUSE HE SHOULD BE GRATEFUL

02:47.434 --> 02:48.901
THAT YOU ASKED HIM
TO PROM.

02:48.903 --> 02:50.402
<i> DEAN:</i>
<i> WHAT COLOUR'S YOUR BOUTONNIER?</i>

02:50.404 --> 02:51.904
UH, WHATEVER COLOUR
MEANS "NO CURFEW

02:51.906 --> 02:52.905
'CAUSE IT'S PROM."

02:52.907 --> 02:54.206
SERIOUSLY?
YEAH,

02:54.207 --> 02:55.506
MY PARENTS HAVE LATE-NIGHT
PLANS OF THEIR OWN.

02:55.509 --> 02:57.409
THEY'RE GOING
TO SOME HOTEL DOWNTOWN.

02:57.411 --> 02:59.444
PLUS THEY TRUST ME.
IT'S WEIRD.

02:59.446 --> 03:01.346
PLUS YOU'RE NOT GONNA
TELL THEM.

03:01.348 --> 03:03.582
(CHUCKLES) SCARY.
JUST LIKE YOUR DAD.

03:03.584 --> 03:05.717
YOU SURE YOU WANNA DATE
A WALKING POLYGRAPH?

03:05.719 --> 03:07.753
(LAUGHS)
YEAH, I'M SURE.

03:07.755 --> 03:09.221
CLARK:
ALL RIGHT.
YOU GUYS NEED A RIDE?

03:09.223 --> 03:10.289
NAH.
WE'RE GONNA BE OKAY, MAN.

03:10.291 --> 03:11.290
CLARK:
ALL RIGHT.
SEE YOU LATER.

03:11.292 --> 03:12.658
DEAN:
LATER.

03:14.195 --> 03:16.395
JULES:
SO YOU'VE MET
MY INFAMOUS BROTHERS.

03:16.397 --> 03:17.521
GOOD TO MEET YOU.

03:17.522 --> 03:18.646
WORDY:
YOU TALKED THE BOSS
OUTTA THE BROWN SUIT.

03:18.647 --> 03:19.771
WELL, WORDY,
SOMEBODY HAD TO.

03:19.772 --> 03:20.896
PARKER:
HEY, I HEARD THAT.

03:22.670 --> 03:23.786
ED:
I MEAN, REALLY,

03:23.787 --> 03:24.903
IT'S A FABULOUS DRESS.
I LIKE IT.

03:24.905 --> 03:26.238
?
YES, DONNA.

03:26.240 --> 03:27.840
SUCH A GENTLEMAN,

03:27.841 --> 03:29.441
AND ALWAYS A KIND WORD;
THAT'S WHY I LOVE YOU.

03:29.443 --> 03:30.442
DEBRIEF WENT LONG;

03:30.444 --> 03:31.743
SOME PEOPLE HAVE
TO WORK HARD.

03:31.745 --> 03:32.945
HOW'S TEAM THREE?

03:32.947 --> 03:34.463
I'M KICKING 'EM
INTO SHAPE.

03:34.464 --> 03:35.980
I TOLD YOU SHE COULDN'T
STAY AWAY FROM THE JOB.

03:35.983 --> 03:37.249
HOW ARE YOU,
WORDY?

03:37.251 --> 03:38.584
I'M GOOD.
GIRLS ARE GOOD.

03:38.586 --> 03:39.718
I MISS THE DAYS THOUGH.

03:39.720 --> 03:41.320
DAYS MISS YOU
RIGHT BACK.

03:41.322 --> 03:42.454
YOU GOING TO THE RECEPTION
TONIGHT?

03:42.456 --> 03:43.972
ABSOLUTELY.

03:43.973 --> 03:45.489
<i> ED:</i>
<i> YOU KNOW WHAT? TEAM ONE'S GOT</i>
<i> A SHIFT TO GET THROUGH FIRST </i>

03:45.492 --> 03:47.426
BECAUSE SOME OF US
WORK EVEN HARDER.

03:47.428 --> 03:48.560
NOT A WORD.
NOT A WORD!

03:53.400 --> 03:56.301
<i> 911 RESPONDER:</i>
<i> YOU'RE DOING GREAT, HON,</i>
<i> STAY WITH ME, OKAY?</i>

03:56.303 --> 03:59.238
I'M GONNA NEED YOU
TO BREATHE OUT FOR ME...

03:59.240 --> 04:00.439
NICE.

04:00.441 --> 04:02.341
<i> FOUR MINUTES</i>
<i> BETWEEN CONTRACTIONS,</i>

04:02.343 --> 04:03.559
<i> WHICH IS AWESOME.</i>

04:03.560 --> 04:04.776
I'M SENDING ALL THIS
TO THE PARAMEDICS

04:04.778 --> 04:07.479
AS SOON AS THEY GET THERE...

04:08.415 --> 04:11.583
<i> WHICH WILL BE IN TWO MINUTES,</i>
<i> OKAY?</i>

04:11.585 --> 04:13.785
<i> YOU GOT A NAME PICKED OUT</i>
<i> FOR THE LITTLE MAN YET?</i>

04:13.787 --> 04:15.420
TRISH:
SO SLOW...

04:15.422 --> 04:16.955
I THINK ONE OF THE SERVERS
NEEDS REBOOTING.

04:16.957 --> 04:18.440
NINA:
(WHISPERS)
CAN YOU DO IT?

04:18.441 --> 04:19.924
I'M WRAPPING UP
THE MIRACLE OF LIFE OVER HERE.

04:19.927 --> 04:21.226
YES.

04:21.227 --> 04:22.526
<i> NINA:</i>
<i> YOU GOT A BAG PACKED</i>
<i> FOR THE HOSPITAL?</i>

04:22.529 --> 04:23.562
<i> NOW DON'T WORRY.</i>

04:23.563 --> 04:24.596
<i> I'M GONNA STAY RIGHT HERE</i>
<i> WITH YOU...</i>

04:31.038 --> 04:34.306
(POWER BUTTON BEEPS,
SERVER REBOOTS)

04:37.444 --> 04:38.577
(SPIKE AND WINNIE LAUGH)

04:38.579 --> 04:39.578
AW...

04:39.580 --> 04:41.313
<i> SPIKE: </i>
<i> I KNOW.</i>

04:41.315 --> 04:42.981
<i> WINNIE:</i>
<i> MAN, GETTING MARRIED</i>
<i> AND GOING TO WORK,</i>

04:42.983 --> 04:44.583
THAT IS DEDICATION.

04:44.585 --> 04:46.551
WELL, IT'S THE ONLY DAY
SAM'S DAD COULD BE HERE.

04:46.553 --> 04:49.855
YOU KNOW, RECEPTION'S
AT THE PARTY BOAT TONIGHT.

04:49.857 --> 04:51.623
I WISH I COULD'VE
BEEN THERE.

04:51.625 --> 04:52.758
ME TOO.

04:52.760 --> 04:54.026
SPIKE,
YOU WERE THERE.

04:54.028 --> 04:55.778
NO, I MEAN I WISH

04:55.779 --> 04:57.529
YOU COULD'VE BEEN THERE
TOO, TOO.

04:57.531 --> 04:58.897
"TOO, TOO?"

04:58.899 --> 05:01.566
"TOO, TOO,"
AS IN TOO, ALSO.

05:01.568 --> 05:02.601
GOTCHA.

05:02.603 --> 05:03.935
(SRU PHONE RINGS)

05:03.937 --> 05:05.220
(PICKS UP)
SRU.

05:05.221 --> 05:06.504
<i> NINA:</i>
<i> HEY, WINNIE,</i>
<i> THIS IS NINA FROM 911.</i>

05:06.507 --> 05:07.862
WINNIE:
HEY, NINA.
WHAT'S GOING ON?

05:07.863 --> 05:09.218
NINA:
WE'VE GOT SOMETHING
IN OUR SERVER ROOM

05:09.219 --> 05:10.574
THAT DOESN'T LOOK LIKE IT
SHOULD BE THERE.

05:10.577 --> 05:12.511
911'S GOT A PROBLEM.

05:12.513 --> 05:13.912
NINA,
I'VE GOT TEAM ONE HERE.

05:13.914 --> 05:15.647
<i> NINA:</i>
<i> IT'S SOME KIND OF A DEVICE</i>
<i> IN A BOX,</i>

05:15.649 --> 05:17.282
IN OUR SERVER ROOM.

05:17.283 --> 05:18.916
IT'S GOT EXPOSED WIRES
AND A BLINKING LIGHT.

05:18.919 --> 05:20.469
ED:
WAS IT LEFT
IN PLAIN SIGHT?

05:20.470 --> 05:22.020
<i> NINA:</i>
<i> NO. NO, IT WAS CONCEALED</i>
<i> IN ONE OF OUR SERVER CABINETS.</i>

05:22.022 --> 05:23.722
WE ONLY FOUND IT
WHEN WE WENT TO DO A REBOOT.

05:23.724 --> 05:25.324
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> GET ANY NON-ESSENTIAL STAFF</i>
<i> OUT OF THERE,</i>

05:25.326 --> 05:26.491
WE'RE ON OUR WAY.

05:26.493 --> 05:27.976
<i> ED:</i>
<i> WINNIE, CALL STAINTON,</i>

05:27.977 --> 05:29.460
GET HIM TO SEE IF THERE'S
A SPIKE IN TERRORIST CHATTER.

05:29.463 --> 05:30.996
YOU GOT IT.

05:30.998 --> 05:32.698
<i> SPIKE?</i>

05:32.700 --> 05:34.833
JUST... YOU KNOW.

05:34.835 --> 05:36.702
I'M ALWAYS CAREFUL.

05:39.039 --> 05:40.906
(SIRENS CHIRP AND WAIL)

05:41.842 --> 05:44.710
(911 STAFF MURMUR, CURIOUS,
TRUCKS ARRIVE, SIRENS WAILING)

05:48.549 --> 05:50.299
ED:
HITTING 911?

05:50.300 --> 05:52.050
PARKER:
THE NERVE CENTRE FOR THE CITY'S
EMERGENCY SERVICES.

05:52.052 --> 05:53.485
SAM:
WE CAN'T SHUT THE PLACE DOWN

05:53.487 --> 05:54.586
WITHOUT LEAVING THE CITY
STRANDED.

05:54.588 --> 05:56.688
BABYCAKES IS READY TO ROLL.

05:57.624 --> 05:59.157
TRISH:
MA'AM, THEY ARE ON THEIR WAY
RIGHT NOW,

05:59.158 --> 06:00.691
SO I'M GONNA NEED YOU
TO CALM DOWN FOR ME, OKAY?

06:00.694 --> 06:02.394
NINA:
WE'RE DOWN TO THREE OPERATORS
AND THREE DISPATCH.

06:02.396 --> 06:04.046
THE EVAC'D STAFF
IS OUT FRONT.

06:04.047 --> 06:05.697
SAM:
'KAY, LEAH, LET'S CHECK OUT
THE REST OF THE BUILDING.

06:05.699 --> 06:07.466
I'M GONNA TALK TO STAFF,
START PROFILING.

06:07.468 --> 06:08.900
ED:
WE'RE GONNA NEED
CCTV FOOTAGE.

06:08.902 --> 06:10.018
ALREADY PULLED IT.
GREAT.

06:10.019 --> 06:11.135
<i> TRISH:</i>
<i> YOU'RE HUSBAND IS PINNED</i>
<i> BY THE STEERING WHEEL,</i>

06:11.138 --> 06:12.671
<i> IS THAT CORRECT?</i>

06:22.583 --> 06:25.484
DAYCARE WORKER:
HOWIE? HOWIE, GIVE ETHAN
HIS BLANKIE BACK, PLEASE.

06:25.486 --> 06:26.852
HOWIE? I NEED YOU TO LISTEN,
OKAY?

06:26.854 --> 06:28.687
THAT BELONGS TO ETHAN,
HONEY.

06:28.689 --> 06:29.721
FINE!

06:29.723 --> 06:32.090
THANK YOU, HOWIE,
GOOD CHOICE.

06:36.530 --> 06:39.931
KIDS:
LET'S GO! BACK AT SCHOOL!
HERE WE COME!

06:39.933 --> 06:42.167
(BABYCAKES WHIRS)

06:48.442 --> 06:49.641
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> I SEE THE BOX.</i>

06:49.643 --> 06:51.410
SENDING OUT ELECTRONIC
COUNTER-MEASURES

06:51.412 --> 06:53.645
AGAINST REMOTE DETONATION.

06:55.716 --> 06:57.816
HA! SEE, ETHAN?
I TOLD YOU WE'D FIND IT.

06:57.818 --> 06:59.184
RUN!

06:59.186 --> 07:01.753
ETHAN:
THERE YOU ARE!
(GIGGLES HAPPILY)

07:03.957 --> 07:07.159
(LOUD BOOM, FIRE ROARS,
GLASS BURSTS)

07:07.161 --> 07:08.727
(DEBRIS CRASHES ALL AROUND)

07:08.729 --> 07:10.529
<i> (PHONES RING OFF THE HOOK)</i>

07:10.531 --> 07:12.030
<i> (OVERLAPPING VOICES</i>
<i> ANSWER CALLS)</i>

07:12.032 --> 07:15.734
TRISH:
911, WHAT IS YOUR EMERGENCY?
SIMCOE AND WELLINGTON?

07:15.736 --> 07:18.136
NINA:
HOW MANY ARE INJURED?
HOW MANY DO YOU SEE?

07:18.138 --> 07:19.771
WHAT'S GOING ON?

07:19.773 --> 07:22.207
NINA:
911, WHAT IS YOUR EMERGENCY?

07:22.209 --> 07:25.644
IT'S A FEDERAL BUILDING,
HEALTH AND WELFARE.

07:26.580 --> 07:27.612
TEAM, WE'RE LOOKING
AT ANOTHER BOMB

07:27.614 --> 07:29.014
THAT JUST WENT OFF DOWNTOWN.

07:29.016 --> 07:30.682
<i> MASS CASUALTIES</i>
<i> IN A BUSY BUILDING -</i>

07:30.684 --> 07:32.684
<i> NO WAY THIS WAS ACCIDENTAL.</i>

07:32.686 --> 07:34.453
WE ARE LOOKING AT TERROR.

07:35.889 --> 07:45.997
¶¶¶

07:45.999 --> 07:51.470
¶¶¶

07:51.472 --> 08:03.882
¶¶¶

08:08.555 --> 08:10.789
<i> (SIRENS WAIL AND CHIRP</i>
<i> IN THE DISTANCE)</i>

08:10.791 --> 08:12.724
<i> NEWS ANCHOR:</i>
<i> IT IS DIFFICULT TO GET</i>
<i> A CLEAR PICTURE,</i>

08:12.726 --> 08:15.894
BUT IT APPEARS THAT
THE EXPLOSION TOOK PLACE...

08:15.896 --> 08:17.512
PARKER:
SPIKE, TALK TO ME.

08:17.513 --> 08:19.129
SPIKE:
I'M WORKING IT,
BUT THIS IS GONNA TAKE TIME.

08:19.132 --> 08:20.232
GUYS, GO.
I GOT THIS.

08:20.234 --> 08:21.533
NO, SPIKE, LISTEN-

08:21.535 --> 08:22.767
ED, GO!

08:22.769 --> 08:24.202
OKAY, COPY!
GUYS, SIMCOE AND WELLINGTON.

08:24.204 --> 08:27.239
SAM, YOU'RE WITH ME.
LET'S MOVE!

08:28.175 --> 08:29.207
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> WE'RE GONNA NEED </i>
<i> ALL EMERGENCY PERSONNEL</i>

08:29.209 --> 08:30.992
<i> ON STANDBY.</i>

08:30.993 --> 08:32.776
CROWD CONTROL,
CASUALTY TRANSPORT.

08:32.779 --> 08:34.246
OKAY, THANK YOU.

08:34.248 --> 08:36.214
NINA, ALL OF YOU HAVE
TO GET OUTSIDE

08:36.216 --> 08:37.576
WITH THE REST
OF YOUR STAFF.

08:37.577 --> 08:38.937
NINA:
WE CAN SPLIT SOME OF THE LOAD
WITH DURHAM REGION,

08:38.938 --> 08:40.298
<i> BUT THEN THEY'LL BE</i>
<i> OVERLOADED.</i>

08:40.299 --> 08:41.659
<i> WE NEED TO STAY</i>
<i> AND KEEP ANSWERING CALLS.</i>

08:41.660 --> 08:43.020
NEGATIVE. THIS BOMB COULD
STILL GO OFF.

08:43.023 --> 08:44.623
THE BOMB COULD STILL
GO OFF,

08:44.625 --> 08:46.625
BUT PEOPLE DEFINITELY NEED
OUR HELP.

08:46.627 --> 08:49.127
<i> IT'S NOT JUST OUR LIVES</i>
<i> ON THE LINE.</i>

08:49.129 --> 08:52.063
(RESPONDERS FRANTICALLY
RESPOND TO CALLS)

08:52.065 --> 08:53.765
OKAY.

08:53.767 --> 08:55.133
WINNIE, I'M NOT LIKING THE WAY
THIS DAY IS GOING.

08:55.135 --> 08:58.036
<i> I NEED ALL SRU TEAMS REUPPED</i>
<i> RIGHT NOW.</i>

08:58.038 --> 08:59.571
YOU GOT IT.

08:59.573 --> 09:01.072
(BABYCAKES WHIRS)

09:01.074 --> 09:03.592
SPIKE:
THE X-RAY IS UP.

09:03.593 --> 09:06.111
I SEE BATTERIES, I SEE WIRES,
I SEE A TIMER...

09:06.113 --> 09:08.547
AND I GOT ANTI-HANDLING
MEASURES.

09:09.283 --> 09:11.583
THIS IS GONNA
COMPLICATE THINGS.

09:11.585 --> 09:13.652
<i> NINA:</i>
<i> PLEASE, MA'AM, </i>
<i> STAY WHERE YOU...</i>

09:13.654 --> 09:14.953
(SIRENS WAIL)

09:15.889 --> 09:17.822
<i> JULES:</i>
<i> EVERYTHING'S FINE, DAD.</i>

09:17.824 --> 09:20.025
JUST MAKING SURE YOU GUYS
GOT ALL CHECKED IN OKAY.

09:20.027 --> 09:21.226
WE'RE GONNA SEE YOU
AT THE HOTEL

09:21.228 --> 09:23.662
<i> AFTER WORK,</i>
<i> ALL RIGHT? </i>

09:23.664 --> 09:24.996
BYE, DAD.

09:26.867 --> 09:28.700
YOU'D DO ANYTHING TO JUST...
WRAP 'EM UP

09:28.702 --> 09:30.201
AND KEEP 'EM SAFE.

09:30.203 --> 09:32.637
YOUR PARENTS WERE IN HAITI
DURING THE EARTHQUAKE, RIGHT?

09:34.174 --> 09:35.273
ALL YOU CAN DO
IS DO YOUR BEST.

09:37.311 --> 09:38.577
YUP.

09:40.113 --> 09:42.213
NO, SOPHIE, I'M OKAY.
I'M OKAY.

09:42.215 --> 09:43.582
LOOK, I'M SURE CLARK'S
OKAY, TOO.

09:43.584 --> 09:44.967
HE'S PROBABLY
JUST SOMEWHERE NOISY,

09:44.968 --> 09:46.351
WHERE HE CAN'T HEAR HIS PHONE,
ALL RIGHT?

09:46.353 --> 09:47.686
<i> I NEED YOU TO CALL ME</i>

09:47.688 --> 09:49.621
AS SOON AS YOU HEAR FROM HIM,
OKAY?

09:49.623 --> 09:51.256
I LOVE YOU.

09:51.258 --> 09:52.257
SHE HEARD ABOUT
THE BOMB?

09:52.259 --> 09:53.775
YEAH.

09:53.776 --> 09:55.292
GUESS YOUR WIFE KNOWS
WHERE YOU ARE.

09:55.295 --> 09:56.661
"WIFE."

09:56.663 --> 09:58.229
FEELS FUNNY, HUH?

09:58.231 --> 09:59.831
IT FEELS GOOD.

09:59.833 --> 10:01.366
SPIKE:
NO CHEMICAL DETECTION,
NO NERVE AGENTS,

10:01.368 --> 10:04.269
NO BLOOD AGENTS,
NO RADIATION.

10:04.271 --> 10:06.004
I'M GOING IN MANUAL.

10:08.275 --> 10:09.741
(BABYCAKES WHIRS)

10:19.786 --> 10:21.119
24 MINUTES.

10:21.121 --> 10:22.988
<i> OKAY.</i>

10:22.990 --> 10:24.673
CAN YOU SEVER
THE POWER SOURCE?

10:24.674 --> 10:26.357
SPIKE:
YEAH, I THINK SO,
BUT IT'S UNDERNEATH.

10:26.360 --> 10:28.293
I CAN'T REACH IT
WITHOUT TRIGGERING

10:28.294 --> 10:30.227
THE ANTI-HANDLING DEVICE
EMBEDDED IN THE C4.

10:30.230 --> 10:32.964
<i> I'M GONNA HAVE TO DISABLE IT</i>
<i> BY HAND.</i>

10:38.271 --> 10:40.839
(KNIFE TOUCHES SOMETHING HARD)

10:47.948 --> 10:49.381
IT'S A MERCURY TILT SWITCH.

10:50.317 --> 10:53.351
<i> THAT DROP SLIDES OVER</i>
<i> BY A HAIR,</i>

10:53.353 --> 10:56.888
AND TOUCHES THOSE TWO WIRES,
AND I LOSE MY 24 MINUTES.

10:56.890 --> 10:58.423
<i> 22 MINUTES.</i>

10:58.424 --> 10:59.957
ED:
HOW DO YOU DISABLE
A MERCURY TILT SWITCH?

10:59.960 --> 11:01.192
ACETONE.

11:01.194 --> 11:02.661
AND WHERE ARE WE GONNA
GET THAT?

11:05.265 --> 11:07.899
(CROWD BUZZES WITH CHATTER)

11:07.901 --> 11:10.168
SPIKE:
(YELLING) ANYBODY HAVE
ANY NAIL POLISH REMOVER?

11:10.170 --> 11:11.903
SERIOUSLY!
ANYBODY?!

11:14.374 --> 11:15.440
THANKS!

11:16.276 --> 11:17.976
ED, THAT WAS STAINTON.

11:17.977 --> 11:19.677
<i> THERE'S BEEN NO CHATTER-SPIKE</i>
<i> ON THE TERRORIST CHANNELS.</i>

11:19.680 --> 11:20.979
<i> ED:</i>
<i> OKAY. THANKS, WINNIE.</i>

11:20.981 --> 11:22.313
SO IF IT IS
A COORDINATED STRIKE,

11:22.315 --> 11:24.249
IT'S A GROUP
THAT'S NOT ON OUR RADAR.

11:24.250 --> 11:26.184
OR IT'S A LONE WOLF
WITH NO GROUP TO CHATTER WITH.

11:26.186 --> 11:28.086
PARKER:
ALL RIGHT, ASSUMING
IT'S THE SAME INDIVIDUAL,

11:28.088 --> 11:29.921
WHAT'S HIS NEXT STEP?

11:29.923 --> 11:31.389
HE HIT THE HEART OF THE CITY'S
DEFENSE SYSTEM

11:31.391 --> 11:32.691
AND A SYMBOL OF GOVERNMENT.

11:32.693 --> 11:33.992
IT SOUNDS MORE POLITICAL
THAN PERSONAL.

11:33.994 --> 11:35.894
HE WANTS TO SHOW HE CAN MAKE
A WHOLE CITY VULNERABLE.

11:35.896 --> 11:37.395
PARKER:
WELL, IF IT IS STATEMENT
ORIENTED,

11:37.397 --> 11:38.730
HE'LL COME OUT
FROM BEHIND THE CURTAIN,

11:38.732 --> 11:40.298
AND SHARE HIS WORLD VIEW.

11:40.300 --> 11:42.367
<i> SPIKE, WHAT'S GOING ON?</i>

11:42.369 --> 11:43.935
SPIKE:
SUBMERGING THE MERCURY
IN ACETONE.

11:43.937 --> 11:45.153
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> TWO MINUTES,</i>

11:45.154 --> 11:46.370
<i> I'M MOVING THE REST</i>
<i> OF THESE PEOPLE OUTTA HERE,</i>

11:46.373 --> 11:47.739
<i> UNLESS YOU TELL ME DIFFERENT.</i>

11:47.741 --> 11:48.807
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> COPY THAT.</i>

11:50.811 --> 11:54.279
ADDING DRY ICE
TO LOWER THE TEMPERATURE.

11:55.182 --> 11:56.381
(DRY ICE FIZZES)

12:02.355 --> 12:03.788
(THERMOMETER BEEPS)

12:04.725 --> 12:05.790
(FIZZING)

12:07.160 --> 12:09.177
MINUS 36 DEGREES...

12:09.178 --> 12:11.195
TWO MORE DEGREES
AND THE MERCURY FREEZES OVER.

12:15.469 --> 12:17.168
COME ON... COME ON...

12:18.105 --> 12:19.404
<i> COME ON!</i>

12:19.406 --> 12:20.872
<i> COME ON!</i>

12:20.874 --> 12:21.873
(FIZZING)

12:21.875 --> 12:23.308
MINUS 38.8 DEGREES.

12:23.310 --> 12:26.311
<i> GOING FOR THE POWER SOURCE.</i>

12:28.982 --> 12:30.315
<i> I SEE IT.</i>

12:32.319 --> 12:34.452
CUTTING THE POWER SUPPLY.

12:36.323 --> 12:38.356
(SNAP) DONE!
WE'RE CLEAR!

12:39.292 --> 12:40.909
(SIGHS WITH RELIEF)

12:40.910 --> 12:42.527
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> CALL CENTRE'S</i>
<i> BACK IN BUSINESS.</i>

12:44.798 --> 12:46.831
WE'RE OKAY;

12:46.833 --> 12:49.901
THE BOMB'S DISABLED,
YOUR COLLEAGUES CAN COME BACK.

12:49.903 --> 12:51.770
(EXHALES, RELIEVED)

12:53.173 --> 12:55.774
(CHOPPER'S ROTORS BEAT LOUDLY)

12:56.510 --> 12:59.844
(SIRENS WAIL,
PEOPLE SHOUT FRANTICALLY)

12:59.846 --> 13:02.180
(SIRENS CHIRP,
HORNS BLAST)

13:08.221 --> 13:12.957
(LOUD BUZZ OF FRANTIC VOICES,
PAPERS FLUTTER IN THE AIR)

13:12.959 --> 13:17.462
(SIRENS WAIL ALL AROUND,
PEOPLE CRY OUT IN DISTRESS)

13:17.464 --> 13:20.231
ED:
OKAY, JULES, LEAH,
HELP EMS IDENTIFY THE WOUNDED,

13:20.233 --> 13:21.399
30 SECONDS PER PATIENT.

13:21.401 --> 13:23.501
SAM, SAME THING INSIDE -
FIND SURVIVORS.

13:23.503 --> 13:24.569
GO!

13:24.571 --> 13:29.541
(PEOPLE SHOUT, SIRENS WAIL,
THE STREET'S IN CHAOS)

13:31.478 --> 13:33.511
ED:
GUYS, REMEMBER,
FOUR LEVELS OF PRIORITY HERE:

13:33.513 --> 13:35.046
GREEN IS FOR MINOR INJURIES;

13:35.048 --> 13:36.080
<i> YELLOW IS FOR URGENT;</i>

13:36.082 --> 13:37.448
RED IS FOR IMMEDIATE.

13:37.450 --> 13:39.367
JULES:
BLACK'S FOR DEAD.

13:39.368 --> 13:41.285
ED:
OR BEYOND SAVING -
IT'S A JUDGMENT CALL HERE.

13:41.288 --> 13:43.454
SIR! SIR!
CAN YOU HEAR ME?

13:44.391 --> 13:45.590
CHECK HIS PULSE.

13:45.592 --> 13:48.126
SIR, I NEED YOU
TO CLOSE YOUR EYES, PLEASE.

13:48.128 --> 13:49.494
OKAY, HE'S IN SHOCK.
RAISE HIS LEGS.

13:49.496 --> 13:52.163
JULES: LET'S PUT THIS UNDER.
LEAH: ALL RIGHT, GENTLY.

13:52.165 --> 13:53.965
ED:
(CALLS OUT)
WE GOT A RED HERE!

13:53.967 --> 13:55.500
TAG AND MOVE!
LET'S GO!

13:55.502 --> 13:57.502
LET'S MOVE!
LET'S MOVE!

13:59.573 --> 14:14.519
¶¶¶

14:14.521 --> 14:24.629
¶¶¶

14:24.631 --> 14:30.201
¶¶¶

14:32.472 --> 14:34.038
TRISH:
911, WHAT IS YOUR EMERGENCY?

14:34.040 --> 14:35.573
NINA:
911, WHAT IS YOUR EMERGENCY?

14:35.575 --> 14:36.608
TRISH:
WHERE ARE YOU LOCATED, SIR?

14:36.610 --> 14:38.576
OKAY, IS ANYONE WITH YOU
RIGHT NOW?

14:38.578 --> 14:42.614
NINA:
NO, STAY ON THE LINE WITH ME.
BREATHE...

14:42.616 --> 14:44.015
PARKER:
WHAT ARE YOU THINKING,
SPIKE?

14:44.016 --> 14:45.415
SPIKE:
I'M THINKING ONE BOMB,
THAT'S PROBABLY YOUR DAY.

14:45.418 --> 14:46.551
TWO BOMBS...

14:46.553 --> 14:49.387
I THINK YOUR DAY
MIGHT NOT BE OVER.

14:49.389 --> 14:50.388
LET'S FIGURE OUT
WHO MADE THIS.

14:50.390 --> 14:52.156
COPY THAT.

14:52.158 --> 14:56.027
<i> NINA:</i>
<i> 911, WHAT IS YOUR EMERGENCY?</i>

14:56.029 --> 14:57.629
LEAH:
MA'AM, CAN YOU HEAR ME?

14:57.631 --> 14:59.564
ARE YOU ABLE TO WALK?

15:00.634 --> 15:02.166
(CALLS OUT)
WE'VE GOT A YELLOW!

15:02.168 --> 15:03.668
JULES:
ALL RIGHT,
PARAMEDICS ARE COMING.

15:03.670 --> 15:05.303
YOU'RE GONNA BE JUST FINE,
OKAY?

15:05.305 --> 15:09.207
LEAH: LET'S GO.
JULES: JUST KEEP ON BREATHING.

15:12.145 --> 15:15.113
ALL RIGHT,
HOLD HER NECK.

15:15.115 --> 15:16.481
<i> LEAH:</i>
<i> MA'AM, CAN YOU HEAR ME?</i>

15:16.483 --> 15:18.383
DAYCARE WORKER 2:
(WEAKLY) ETHAN...

15:18.385 --> 15:19.450
ETHAN...

15:20.654 --> 15:21.920
<i> ETHAN...</i>

15:27.427 --> 15:29.260
OKAY... HI, HONEY.

15:30.196 --> 15:31.629
MY NAME IS JULES.

15:32.565 --> 15:34.532
I'M GONNA HELP YOU,
OKAY?

15:35.468 --> 15:36.534
(NO RESPONSE)

15:41.107 --> 15:43.241
(JULES WELLS UP,
WEEPING)

15:57.023 --> 15:59.657
I'M SO SORRY...
I'M SO SORRY, HONEY.

16:03.697 --> 16:05.697
(WEEPING)

16:05.699 --> 16:07.332
<i> LEAH:</i>
<i> (PANICKED) JULES!</i>

16:07.333 --> 16:08.966
SHE SAYS THERE'S A DAYCARE
IN THERE.

16:08.969 --> 16:10.601
THERE'S MORE KIDS!

16:10.603 --> 16:12.704
<i> ED! INSIDE!</i>
<i> THERE'S A DAYCARE!</i>

16:12.706 --> 16:14.572
<i> ED:</i>
<i> COPY! SAM,</i>
<i> CHECK THE FLOORPLANS;</i>

16:14.574 --> 16:15.606
<i> WE GOTTA GET THERE.</i>

16:15.608 --> 16:17.308
I'M ON IT!

16:17.309 --> 16:19.009
<i> ED:</i>
<i> MA'AM, SOMEBODY'S GONNA BE</i>
<i> RIGHT WITH YOU, ALL RIGHT?</i>

16:22.716 --> 16:24.215
JULES:
IS THIS THE DAYCARE?

16:24.217 --> 16:25.450
SAM:
I CAN HEAR A WOMAN, KIDS.

16:25.452 --> 16:27.318
SOMEBODY MIGHT BE HURT,
I CAN'T BE SURE.

16:27.320 --> 16:30.488
JULES:
(CALLING OUT) HELLO!
THIS IS THE POLICE!

16:30.490 --> 16:32.557
<i> WE'RE GONNA HELP YOU!</i>
<i> CAN YOU HEAR US?</i>

16:32.559 --> 16:34.692
ED:
GUYS, THE DAYCARE'S FRONT DOOR'S
FIFTEEN FEET IN.

16:34.694 --> 16:36.361
THEY CAN'T HEAR US
WITH ALL THIS DEBRIS.

16:36.363 --> 16:37.662
SAM:
CONTROLLED DEMOLITION
TO OPEN THE WAY?

16:37.664 --> 16:39.631
<i> ED:</i>
<i> SAM, WE CAN'T DO IT.</i>

16:39.632 --> 16:41.599
IT'S TOO UNSTABLE.
WE GOTTA GO IN.

16:41.600 --> 16:43.567
<i> DAYCARE WORKER:</i>
<i> (THROUGH PARABOLIC MIC)</i>
<i> SASHA, PLEASE, HONEY,</i>
<i> STAY CALM ALL RIGHT? </i>

16:43.570 --> 16:44.803
SAM:
YOU GONNA FIT THROUGH
THAT HOLE?

16:44.804 --> 16:46.037
<i> DAYCARE WORKER:</i>
<i> WE'RE GONNA GET OUTTA HERE,</i>
<i> OKAY?</i>

16:46.039 --> 16:47.572
ED:
I'M GONNA TRY.

16:47.574 --> 16:51.642
(RUBBLE GROANS AND SHIFTS,
COLLAPSING FURTHER)

16:52.579 --> 16:55.580
SAM:
ED, THERE'S NO WAY,
IT'S TOO RISKY!

16:55.582 --> 16:57.415
<i> DAYCARE WORKER:</i>
<i> JUST... JUST LEAVE HOWIE!</i>

16:57.417 --> 16:59.050
<i> LOOK,</i>
<i> HE CAN'T MOVE RIGHT NOW.</i>

16:59.052 --> 17:00.251
<i> HE'S... HE'S SLEEPING.</i>
<i> (KID CRIES IN BACKGROUND)</i>

17:00.253 --> 17:01.669
JULES:
(UPSET) OKAY,
THERE'S A KID...

17:01.670 --> 17:03.086
THERE'S A KID PINNED DOWN
IN THERE.

17:03.089 --> 17:04.756
I'M SMALL ENOUGH;
I CAN FIT THROUGH THAT HOLE.

17:04.758 --> 17:06.591
ED:
JULES, THE STRUCTURE'S
BEEN COMPROMISED HERE.

17:06.593 --> 17:08.526
WE CAN'T LET YOU GO IN,
IT MIGHT COLLAPSE.

17:08.528 --> 17:09.694
I CAN DO THIS!

17:09.695 --> 17:10.861
SAM:
JULES, STOP.
WE'LL FIND ANOTHER WAY.

17:10.862 --> 17:12.028
JULES:
SAM, YOU'VE GOTTA
LET ME DO THIS!

17:12.029 --> 17:13.195
JULES, YOU'RE NOT
THINKING STRAIGHT!

17:13.196 --> 17:14.362
THERE ARE CHILDREN
IN THERE

17:14.367 --> 17:15.500
AND WE ARE RUNNING
OUT OF TIME!

17:15.502 --> 17:16.801
NOW, SAM, RIGHT NOW,

17:16.803 --> 17:19.804
ARE YOU MY TEAMMATE
OR MY HUSBAND?!

17:23.476 --> 17:25.476
(DETERMINED)
I CAN DO THIS.

17:25.478 --> 17:26.744
ED:
LET'S GO. LET'S GO.

17:26.746 --> 17:30.681
JULES:
(CALLING OUT)
HELLO! I'M COMING IN!

17:30.683 --> 17:32.550
(STRUGGLING GRUNTS)

17:42.695 --> 17:44.562
(CAR PUTTERS ALONG)

17:53.807 --> 17:55.106
(SHOCKED, FRANTIC CHATTER)

17:55.108 --> 17:58.109
<i> WOMAN:</i>
<i> WHAT'S HAPPENING HERE?</i>

17:58.845 --> 18:00.445
MIRA:
OH MY GOD...

18:03.316 --> 18:05.316
(LOUD BOOM NEARBY,
ANOTHER EXPLOSION)

18:05.318 --> 18:07.452
(PANICKED GASPS AND SHOUTS)

18:08.388 --> 18:09.720
TRISH:
OH MY GOD...

18:09.722 --> 18:11.522
ANOTHER BOMB'S GONE OFF!

18:12.459 --> 18:14.358
(FRANTIC CHATTER
THROUGHOUT CALL CENTRE)

18:14.360 --> 18:15.993
NINA:
SIR, COULD YOU REPEAT THAT,
PLEASE?

18:15.994 --> 18:17.627
TRISH:
I'M SORRY, MA'AM,
I'M HAVING TROUBLE HEARING YOU,

18:17.630 --> 18:19.530
<i> DID YOU SAY CITY HALL?</i>

18:19.532 --> 18:21.566
(PHONE BUZZES)

18:21.568 --> 18:23.568
<i> NINA:</i>
<i> SERGEANT,</i>

18:23.570 --> 18:25.169
WE HAVE A MAN
CLAIMING RESPONSIBILITY.

18:25.171 --> 18:27.605
HE WANTS TO TALK
TO THE "DECISIONMAKER."

18:27.607 --> 18:30.842
(PHONES RING,
RESPONDERS ANSWER CALLS)

18:31.778 --> 18:33.467
THIS IS SERGEANT GREG PARKER

18:33.468 --> 18:35.157
WITH THE POLICE STRATEGIC
RESPONSE UNIT.

18:35.158 --> 18:36.847
<i> DIGITALLY ALTERED MALE VOICE:</i>
<i> YOUR RANK DOESN'T IMPRESS ME.</i>

18:36.850 --> 18:38.483
<i> ARE YOU THE ONE</i>
<i> RUNNING THE SHOW?</i>

18:38.485 --> 18:40.785
SIR, VERY BUSY DOWN HERE.
I'M GONNA HAVE TO HANG UP

18:40.787 --> 18:43.354
IF I'M NOT CONVINCED YOU ARE
WHAT YOU SAY YOU ARE.

18:43.356 --> 18:45.456
I'M GONNA GIVE YOU TEN SECONDS.
NINE, EIGHT...

18:45.458 --> 18:47.325
<i> MALE VOICE:</i>
<i> THE BUILDING YOU'RE IN</i>
<i> IS STILL STANDING.</i>

18:47.327 --> 18:48.326
<i> NICE WORK, PUPPET.</i>

18:48.328 --> 18:49.327
I'M LISTENING.

18:49.329 --> 18:50.528
<i> MALE VOICE:</i>
<i> THREE BOMBS...</i>

18:50.530 --> 18:51.662
<i> YOU THINK IT ENDS THERE,</i>
<i> BUT IT DOESN'T.</i>

18:51.664 --> 18:53.042
PARKER:
WHOA...

18:53.043 --> 18:54.421
<i> MALE VOICE:</i>
<i> THIS IS JUST THE BEGINNING.</i>

18:54.422 --> 18:55.800
PARKER:
SIR, THERE ARE MORE BOMBS?
HOW MANY MORE?

18:55.802 --> 18:57.268
<i> MALE VOICE:</i>
<i> LOTS MORE.</i>

18:57.270 --> 18:58.503
<i> SHOULDN'T BE LONG</i>
<i> 'TIL THE NEXT ONE.</i>

18:58.505 --> 18:59.637
HOW LONG, SIR?

18:59.639 --> 19:01.372
<i> MALE VOICE:</i>
<i> ABOUT HALF AN HOUR,</i>

19:01.374 --> 19:03.274
<i> AND ONE AFTER THAT,</i>
<i> AND AFTER THAT...</i>

19:03.276 --> 19:04.642
LOOK, WHO IS THIS?

19:06.679 --> 19:08.446
WHO IS THIS?!

19:08.448 --> 19:10.915
YOU'RE TALKING TO THE ONE
RUNNING THE SHOW.

19:10.917 --> 19:13.317
(LINE CLICKS
AS HE HANGS UP)

19:19.225 --> 19:22.793
(DISTANT EERIE HOWL
OF CAR ALARMS AND SIRENS)

19:22.795 --> 19:24.762
<i> NEWS ANCHOR:</i>
<i> A SECOND DETONATION</i>
<i> IN THE DOWNTOWN CORE</i>

19:24.764 --> 19:26.898
<i> HAS GIVEN WEIGHT</i>
<i> TO THE SPECULATION</i>

19:26.900 --> 19:29.767
<i> THAT THESE INCIDENTS</i>
<i> ARE TERROR-RELATED. </i>

19:29.769 --> 19:31.536
BUT WE REPEAT,

19:31.538 --> 19:34.639
THIS IS ONLY SPECULATION
AT THIS POINT.

19:34.641 --> 19:38.442
<i> ALL NON-CRITICAL CASUALTIES</i>
<i> ARE BEING TRANSPORTED...</i>

19:38.444 --> 19:41.579
<i> NINA:</i>
<i> BUT WHAT'S AVAILABLE?</i>

19:41.581 --> 19:44.215
EVERY TRUCK YOU CAN SPARE,
EVERY AMBULANCE, EVERY CREW,

19:44.217 --> 19:46.184
WE NEED THEM ON THE ROAD
TO TORONTO IMMEDIATELY.

19:46.186 --> 19:47.718
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> I UNDERSTAND.</i>
<i> (PHONE BEEPS OFF)</i>

19:47.720 --> 19:49.220
ALL RIGHT, TEAM,
THEY'VE JUST UPGRADED THIS THING

19:49.222 --> 19:51.455
TO A CATEGORY ONE EMERGENCY.

19:51.457 --> 19:53.457
<i> FIRE AND EMS FROM DURHAM</i>
<i> ARE ON THEIR WAY.</i>

19:53.459 --> 19:55.293
<i> WE'RE REACHING OUT TO HALTON,</i>
<i> PEEL AND YORK.</i>

19:55.295 --> 19:56.727
<i> IT'S ALL HANDS ON DECK.</i>

19:56.729 --> 19:58.262
SAM:
HAVE YOU CONTACTED
THE MILITARY?

19:58.264 --> 20:00.364
(PARKER'S CELL BUZZES)

20:01.301 --> 20:02.900
PARKER:
YEAH, WE'VE GOT UNITS
FROM CFB BORDEN.

20:02.902 --> 20:04.902
THEY'RE GONNA CONTROL
THE STREETS

20:04.903 --> 20:06.903
AND SET UP A MASS CASUALTY
TRIAGE AT THE STADIUM,

20:06.906 --> 20:08.873
<i> ALL THE HOSPITALS</i>
<i> ARE GONNA BE OVER CAPACITY.</i>

20:08.875 --> 20:10.341
WINNIE:
ED, I'VE GOT YOUR WIFE
ON THE LINE.

20:10.342 --> 20:11.808
ED:
WINNIE, TELL HER I'LL CALL HER
AS SOON AS I CAN.

20:11.811 --> 20:13.211
TELL HER WHAT'S GOING ON HERE.

20:13.213 --> 20:14.946
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> SPIKE, WHAT'RE WE LOOKING AT?</i>

20:14.948 --> 20:17.248
SPIKE:
I CAN'T TRACE IT.
IT'S A DISPOSABLE CELL.

20:17.250 --> 20:18.749
THE VOICE HAS BEEN
DIGITALLY ALTERED.

20:18.751 --> 20:19.917
<i> I CAN'T UNSCRAMBLE IT</i>

20:19.919 --> 20:21.252
BUT IT'S A FAIR GUESS
IT'S A "HE."

20:21.254 --> 20:22.253
THAT NARROWS IT DOWN.

20:22.255 --> 20:23.354
ANYTHING IN THE BACKGROUND?

20:23.355 --> 20:24.454
NO. I'VE FILTERED IT,
I'VE BOOSTED IT,

20:24.457 --> 20:25.923
BUT ALL I'M GETTING IS HIM.

20:25.925 --> 20:28.259
<i> MALE VOICE:</i>
<i> YOUR RANK DOESN'T</i>
<i> IMPRESS ME.</i>

20:28.261 --> 20:30.028
<i> ARE YOU THE ONE</i>
<i> RUNNING THE SHOW?</i>

20:30.029 --> 20:31.796
PARKER:
HE HATES AUTHORITY.
HE'S SETTING HIS OWN TERMS.

20:31.798 --> 20:33.297
<i> MALE VOICE:</i>
<i> THE BUILDING YOU'RE IN</i>
<i> IS STILL STANDING.</i>

20:33.299 --> 20:34.398
<i> NICE WORK, PUPPET!</i>

20:34.400 --> 20:35.399
"PUPPET."

20:35.401 --> 20:37.868
HE'S THE MASTER...

20:37.870 --> 20:39.637
AND HE'S PULLING ALL
THE STRINGS.

20:40.573 --> 20:43.341
(PHONES RING,
RESPONDERS ANSWER)

20:43.343 --> 20:45.309
<i> (SOUND OF VOICES NEARBY)</i>

20:45.311 --> 20:46.978
JULES:
(CALLS OUT) HELLO!

20:46.980 --> 20:49.313
(DEBRIS SCRAPES)
CAN YOU HEAR ME?!

20:49.315 --> 20:50.281
<i> DAYCARE WORKER:</i>
<i> (SLIGHTLY MUFFLED)</i>
<i> HEY! HEY! OVER HERE!</i>

20:50.283 --> 20:51.482
JULES:
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?!

20:51.484 --> 20:53.401
<i> DELLA:</i>
<i> DELLA!</i>

20:53.402 --> 20:55.319
JULES:
DELLA, MY NAME'S JULES.
MY TEAM'S HERE.

20:55.321 --> 20:56.787
WE'RE GONNA COME GET YOU,
OKAY?

20:56.789 --> 20:58.022
<i> DELLA:</i>
<i> THERE'S A HURT LITTLE BOY</i>
<i> IN HERE!</i>

20:58.024 --> 20:59.390
<i> PLEASE HURRY!</i>

20:59.392 --> 21:00.958
(WHISPERS)
CAREFUL, JULES.

21:04.831 --> 21:06.330
(JULES CRIES OUT IN PAIN)

21:06.332 --> 21:07.331
SAM:
JULES!

21:07.333 --> 21:09.333
ED:
JULES, WHAT'S GOING ON?!

21:09.335 --> 21:11.769
JULES:
(TAKING DEEP BREATHS)

21:11.771 --> 21:13.271
I'M OKAY.

21:13.273 --> 21:16.540
<i> REBAR DUG INTO MY LEG.</i>
<i> I'M OKAY.</i>

21:16.542 --> 21:19.677
(GRUNTS IN PAIN
AS SHE MOVES FORWARD)

21:22.715 --> 21:24.048
(PARKER'S CELL BUZZES)

21:24.984 --> 21:26.851
PARKER:
(PHONE BEEPS)
DEAN. SON.

21:26.853 --> 21:29.353
DEAN:
DAD. (SIGHS, RELIEVED)

21:29.355 --> 21:30.788
YOU DIDN'T ANSWER.
I JUST...

21:30.790 --> 21:31.789
WE DIDN'T KNOW.

21:31.791 --> 21:32.790
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> I'M FINE, I'M FINE.</i>

21:32.792 --> 21:34.081
DEAN:
ED?

21:34.082 --> 21:35.371
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> ED'S FINE,</i>
<i> WE'RE ALL FINE.</i>

21:35.372 --> 21:36.661
HOW ABOUT YOU?
YOU'RE STILL AT SCHOOL, RIGHT?

21:36.663 --> 21:37.995
DEAN:
IT'S STUDY DAY,
REMEMBER?

21:37.997 --> 21:40.698
I'M DOWNTOWN WITH MIRA,
WE'RE SHOPPING FOR PROM.

21:40.700 --> 21:41.699
(ALARMED)
WHERE ARE YOU?

21:41.701 --> 21:42.700
<i> DEAN:</i>
<i> I'M ON GERRARD.</i>

21:42.702 --> 21:44.035
PARKER:
IS CLARK WITH YOU?

21:44.037 --> 21:45.403
DEAN:
(WORRIED) HE WAS.
HE SPLIT OFF, DAD.

21:45.405 --> 21:46.404
HE WENT TO GET A PERMIT.

21:46.406 --> 21:47.705
PARKER:
A PERMIT FOR WHAT?

21:47.706 --> 21:49.005
DEAN:
FOR THE PROM -
THAT OUTDOOR PARTY.

21:49.008 --> 21:50.007
DO YOU KNOW WHERE?

21:50.009 --> 21:51.409
<i> DEAN:</i>
<i> NO.</i>

21:51.411 --> 21:52.843
PARKER:
DID YOU TRY HIS CELL?

21:52.845 --> 21:54.845
YEAH, NO ANSWER.
DAD, WHAT'S GOING ON?

21:54.847 --> 21:56.647
EVERYBODY'S FREAKING OUT,
THEY'RE SAYING IT'S TERRORISM.

21:56.649 --> 21:58.349
PARKER:
DEAN, WE'RE FIGURING IT OUT,
BUDDY, ALL RIGHT?

21:58.351 --> 21:59.617
I WANT YOU AND MIRA
TO GO TO THE STATION.

21:59.619 --> 22:00.618
<i> WAIT FOR ME THERE.</i>

22:00.620 --> 22:01.986
DEAN:
OKAY.

22:01.987 --> 22:03.353
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> DON'T GO INTO THE SUBWAYS</i>
<i> AND AVOID PUBLIC BUILDINGS,</i>

22:03.356 --> 22:04.355
YOU HEAR ME?

22:04.357 --> 22:05.756
<i> AVOID PUBLIC BUILDINGS.</i>

22:05.758 --> 22:08.059
JUST KEEP YOUR EYES OPEN,
ALL RIGHT?

22:08.061 --> 22:09.093
DEAN?

22:09.095 --> 22:10.661
(LINE GOES DEAD)

22:10.663 --> 22:12.330
PARKER:
DEAN. DEANO!

22:13.066 --> 22:14.716
(COMPUTER BEEPS)

22:14.717 --> 22:16.367
NINA:
HEY, WE JUST LOST A WHOLE
CELL PHONE ZONE DOWNTOWN.

22:16.369 --> 22:17.424
LINES ARE OVERLOADED.

22:17.425 --> 22:18.480
PARKER:
THAT'S JUST GONNA ACCELERATE
EVERYBODY.

22:18.481 --> 22:19.536
SPIKE:
THAT'S JUST WHAT
OUR GUY WANTS -

22:19.539 --> 22:20.939
FEAR FOR FEAR'S SAKE.

22:20.940 --> 22:22.340
PARKER:
WHAT IF WE MAKE
A PUBLIC ANNOUNCEMENT ON TV,

22:22.342 --> 22:23.564
ACKNOWLEDGE
WHAT'S HAPPENING HERE.

22:23.565 --> 22:24.787
SPIKE:
IT'LL MAKE OUR GUY
EVEN HAPPIER.

22:24.788 --> 22:26.010
MORE ATTENTION,
MORE VALIDATION,

22:26.012 --> 22:27.261
MORE MASS PANIC.

22:27.262 --> 22:28.511
PARKER:
BUT IF WE DON'T WARN PEOPLE
TO BE VIGILANT,

22:28.514 --> 22:29.613
WE COULD BE PUTTING THEM
AT RISK.

22:29.615 --> 22:31.816
FEAR'S ABOUT
NOT HAVING ANSWERS.

22:31.818 --> 22:33.484
WINNIE,
GET ME THE MAYOR'S OFFICE.

22:33.486 --> 22:34.819
WE NEED TO GO PUBLIC, NOW.

22:34.821 --> 22:36.354
SOMEONE NEEDS TO TALK
TO THE CITY.

22:36.356 --> 22:37.889
<i> WINNIE:</i>
<i> COPY.</i>

22:37.890 --> 22:39.423
(DELLA'S MUFFLED VOICE CARRIES
AS SHE REASSURES KIDS)

22:39.425 --> 22:41.926
JULES:
I SEE IT!
THE DAYCARE'S UP AHEAD.

22:41.928 --> 22:43.861
(RUBBLE SCRAPES
AS JULES CLEARS PATH)

22:43.863 --> 22:45.379
<i> DELLA:</i>
<i> WE'RE GONNA BE OKAY.</i>

22:45.380 --> 22:46.896
<i> WE'RE GONNA GET OUTTA HERE</i>
<i> AND WE'RE GONNA BE OKAY.</i>

22:46.899 --> 22:48.366
(JULES GRUNTS,
VENT CRASHES)

22:48.368 --> 22:49.967
BOY:
THERE'S SOMEONE HERE!

22:49.969 --> 22:51.135
DELLA:
(GASPS) OH, THANK GOD!

22:51.137 --> 22:53.137
OH MY GOD!
YOU HAVE TO HELP HIM!

22:53.139 --> 22:56.040
PLEASE! PLEASE!
YOU HAVE TO HELP HIM!

22:56.042 --> 22:57.475
(PANICKED)
HE'S STUCK THERE!
PLEASE!

22:57.477 --> 22:58.943
DELLA. DELLA!

22:58.945 --> 23:00.611
DELLA, STOP IT!
LOOK AT ME.

23:00.613 --> 23:01.612
YOU'VE HELD IT TOGETHER
FOR THESE KIDS

23:01.614 --> 23:03.381
THIS LONG, OKAY?

23:03.383 --> 23:04.482
YOU JUST NEED TO KEEP ON
DOING THAT.

23:04.484 --> 23:06.450
JUST KEEP BREATHING.

23:06.452 --> 23:07.418
(CALMS A BIT)

23:07.420 --> 23:08.519
LET'S GO.
OKAY...

23:08.521 --> 23:10.521
COME ON,
COME ON.

23:14.994 --> 23:17.561
HI, HONEY.
CAN YOU TALK TO ME?

23:19.465 --> 23:21.565
BUDDY?

23:21.567 --> 23:23.434
BUDDY!
(HOWIE STIRS, MOANS)

23:23.436 --> 23:26.570
HI! HI. ARE YOU OKAY?

23:26.572 --> 23:27.905
<i> I'M GONNA GET YOU</i>
<i> OUTTA HERE.</i>

23:30.643 --> 23:33.043
ALL RIGHT, DELLA,
I WANT YOU TO GATHER THE KIDS,

23:33.045 --> 23:35.579
<i> GET THEM READY.</i>

23:35.580 --> 23:38.114
WHEN I GET OUR FRIEND OUT,
WE'RE GONNA GO.

23:38.117 --> 23:39.984
WANNA SEE HOW STRONG I AM?

23:39.986 --> 23:41.419
YEAH?

23:41.421 --> 23:42.820
DELLA:
IT'S GONNA BE OKAY,
ALL RIGHT?

23:42.822 --> 23:44.121
<i> WE'RE GONNA GO HOME SOON.</i>

23:44.123 --> 23:45.523
<i> CHILD:</i>
<i> I'M SCARED.</i>

23:46.759 --> 23:48.959
(JULES GRUNTS IN PAIN)

23:48.961 --> 23:50.761
UNGH!
THAT'S MY JACK!

23:50.763 --> 23:52.930
LET'S SEE HOW STRONG
I AM.

23:53.866 --> 23:56.534
(PUMPS JACK,
DEBRIS CRUMBLES)

23:58.638 --> 24:00.471
JULES: DO YOU FEEL THAT?
HOWIE: MM-HMM.

24:00.473 --> 24:01.706
JULES:
GOOD. CAN YOU MOVE YOUR LEGS?

24:01.707 --> 24:02.940
HOWIE: (MOANS) YEAH...
JULES: YEAH?

24:02.942 --> 24:04.508
DELLA:
(SIGHS WITH RELIEF)

24:04.510 --> 24:06.544
(JULES AND HOWIE GRUNT
AS SHE PULLS HIM FREE)

24:06.546 --> 24:09.146
JULES:
LET'S GET YOU TO YOUR MOM.
HOW 'BOUT THAT?

24:09.148 --> 24:11.015
HE'S OKAY.
LET'S GO.

24:11.017 --> 24:13.301
<i> CHILD:</i>
<i> I MISS MY MOM.</i>

24:13.302 --> 24:15.586
<i> JULES:</i>
<i> LET'S GO! WE'RE GONNA</i>
<i> GET YOU OUTTA HERE, OKAY?</i>

24:15.588 --> 24:19.190
YES, SIR, I UNDERSTAND.
I WILL DO MY BEST.

24:19.192 --> 24:20.958
THE MAYOR GOT CAUGHT
IN THE BLAST AT CITY HALL.

24:20.960 --> 24:22.493
HE'S BEING TREATED.
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

24:22.495 --> 24:23.661
THE DEPUTY MAYOR
WANTS A UNIFORM

24:23.663 --> 24:24.862
TO TALK TO THE CITY.

24:24.864 --> 24:26.730
BOSS,
NO ONE BETTER.

24:27.667 --> 24:30.000
LET'S GET YOU SET UP.

24:33.773 --> 24:37.241
JULES, DELLA AND KIDS:
(GRUNTING AND COUGHING)

24:38.177 --> 24:39.743
(GRUNTS OF EFFORT)

24:42.181 --> 24:49.186
¶¶¶

24:50.122 --> 24:53.257
(GRUNTS OF EFFORT)

24:56.229 --> 25:11.141
¶¶¶

25:11.143 --> 25:25.723
¶¶¶

25:26.659 --> 25:29.593
<i> NEWS ANCHOR:</i>
<i> WE GO NOW TO THIS CRITICAL</i>
<i> INCIDENT'S OFFICER IN CHARGE,</i>

25:29.595 --> 25:31.028
SERGEANT GREGORY PARKER

25:31.030 --> 25:34.298
FROM THE POLICE SERVICE'S
STRATEGIC RESPONSE UNIT.

25:34.300 --> 25:35.733
SERGEANT?

25:35.735 --> 25:37.835
YOU'RE PROBABLY AWARE

25:37.836 --> 25:39.936
THAT THE CITY'S FACING
AN EMERGENCY SITUATION;

25:39.939 --> 25:42.273
TWO EXPLOSIONS
RIGHT IN THE HEART OF OUR CITY.

25:42.275 --> 25:43.791
I WANT YOU TO KNOW

25:43.792 --> 25:45.308
THAT WE'VE GOT A LOT
OF GOOD FOLKS ON THE CASE,

25:45.311 --> 25:48.078
<i> RESPONDERS FROM THE CITY </i>
<i> AND FROM SURROUNDING REGIONS</i>

25:48.080 --> 25:50.281
<i> ARE ALL WORKING TOGETHER</i>
<i> TO KEEP YOU SAFE,</i>

25:50.283 --> 25:52.983
AND TO KEEP EVERYTHING
UNDER CONTROL.

25:52.985 --> 25:54.585
<i> NOW, YOU'RE GONNA HEAR</i>
<i> A LOT OF SPECULATION</i>

25:54.587 --> 25:56.871
<i> AND MAYBE SOME RUMOURS,</i>

25:56.872 --> 25:59.156
<i>'CAUSE THAT'S JUST WHAT HAPPENS</i>
<i> IN A SITUATION LIKE THIS,</i>

25:59.158 --> 26:01.258
<i>AND SOME OF IT MAY BE ALARMING.</i>

26:01.260 --> 26:04.295
BUT I WANNA TELL YOU
THAT THE BEST WAY TO STAY SAFE

26:04.297 --> 26:07.298
IS TO STAY CALM AND TO LOOK OUT
AFTER EACH OTHER.

26:07.300 --> 26:09.767
HIGHWAYS, ROADS, CELL PHONES,
911 -

26:09.769 --> 26:12.069
PLEASE USE THESE AS SPARINGLY
AS YOU CAN

26:12.071 --> 26:14.572
BECAUSE IF THESE SYSTEMS
ARE OVERLOADED

26:14.574 --> 26:16.307
THEY WILL SHUT DOWN.

26:17.710 --> 26:19.010
<i> TODAY IS THE KIND OF DAY</i>

26:19.011 --> 26:20.311
<i> THAT WE'LL ALL LOOK BACK AT,</i>
<i> YEARS FROM NOW,</i>

26:20.313 --> 26:22.146
<i> AND REMEMBER EXACTLY</i>
<i> WHERE WE WERE</i>

26:22.148 --> 26:24.348
<i> AND WHAT WE DID.</i>

26:24.350 --> 26:25.849
<i> WE HAVE A CHANCE</i>
<i> TO MAKE CHOICES HERE</i>

26:25.851 --> 26:28.085
<i> THAT WE WILL BE PROUD OF.</i>

26:28.087 --> 26:31.121
<i> TODAY'S THE DAY THAT WE DID</i>
<i> NOT LET FEAR BREAK US DOWN,</i>

26:31.123 --> 26:33.324
<i> AND TURN US AGAINST</i>
<i> EACH OTHER.</i>

26:33.326 --> 26:36.860
THIS WAS THE DAY
THAT WE TOOK CARE OF EACH OTHER.

26:37.897 --> 26:41.165
<i> THE DAY THAT WE SAID NO</i>
<i> TO TERROR,</i>

26:41.167 --> 26:42.700
TOGETHER.

26:45.304 --> 26:47.104
<i> I WANT US ALL TO THINK ABOUT</i>

26:47.106 --> 26:48.973
<i> HOW WE WANT TO REMEMBER</i>
<i> THIS DAY.</i>

26:50.376 --> 26:52.009
<i> IT'S UP TO US.</i>

26:53.946 --> 26:56.380
<i> I WANT TO THANK YOU</i>
<i> FOR YOUR ATTENTION,</i>

26:56.382 --> 26:59.116
<i> AND FOR YOUR COURAGE.</i>

26:59.118 --> 27:01.919
<i> NEWS ANCHOR:</i>
<i> THANK YOU, SERGEANT PARKER.</i>
<i> WE RETURN NOW TO OUR LIVE...</i>

27:01.921 --> 27:04.188
WHAT'D YOU THINK, SPIKE?
CHEESY?

27:04.190 --> 27:05.656
NOT CHEESY, BOSS.

27:08.928 --> 27:09.994
(SIGHS)

27:14.400 --> 27:16.333
PARAMEDIC:
YOU GOTTA STAY OFF THIS LEG.

27:16.335 --> 27:17.701
HOW'S THE PAIN?

27:17.703 --> 27:19.269
(IGNORING IT)
PAIN'S PAIN.

27:20.873 --> 27:22.673
ED:
WELL, WHAT DO MEAN
THE BOYS ARE DOWNTOWN?

27:22.675 --> 27:24.341
<i> PARKER</i>
<i> THEY WENT SHOPPING TOGETHER,</i>
<i> THEN CLARK SPLIT OFF.</i>

27:24.343 --> 27:25.809
THAT'S ALL I KNOW.

27:25.811 --> 27:27.011
ED:
WELL, DID HE SAY WHERE
HE WAS GOING?

27:27.013 --> 27:28.345
PARKER:
TO GET A PERMIT FOR A PARTY.

27:28.347 --> 27:30.347
ED:
GREG, THAT'S AT
A MUNICIPAL BUILDING.

27:30.348 --> 27:32.348
I, I... I HAVEN'T BEEN ABLE
TO GET A HOLD OF HIM.

27:32.351 --> 27:35.019
PARKER:
EDDIE, I'M SURE HE'S FINE.
IT'S PROBABLY CELL TOWERS.

27:35.021 --> 27:36.353
ED:
(PANICKED) WELL...
WELL, WHAT AM I GONNA DO?

27:36.355 --> 27:37.855
WHAT DO I...
WHAT AM I GONNA SAY TO SOPHIE?

27:37.857 --> 27:39.056
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> LOOK, ED,</i>

27:39.058 --> 27:40.357
JUST WAIT TILL WE HAVE
MORE INFORMATION,

27:40.359 --> 27:41.992
BEFORE SHE GETS WORRIED
FOR NOTHING.

27:41.994 --> 27:43.360
ED!
OKAY,
I'LL FIGURE IT OUT.

27:43.362 --> 27:44.361
I GOTTA GO.
YEAH?

27:44.362 --> 27:45.361
<i> LEAH:</i>
<i> I GOT A CASUALTY REPORT.</i>

27:45.364 --> 27:46.363
WHAT DO WE GOT?

27:46.365 --> 27:48.265
FORTY-ONE GREEN,
ELEVEN YELLOW,

27:48.267 --> 27:50.801
SEVENTEEN RED,
AND TOO MANY DEAD.

27:50.803 --> 27:52.336
WHOEVER DID THIS...

27:52.337 --> 27:53.870
IS GONNA GET HIS ASS
NAILED TO THE WALL.

27:53.873 --> 27:55.706
OKAY. THANKS, LEAH.

27:55.708 --> 27:56.757
DONNA:
HEY. WE'RE DONE TAGGING.

27:56.758 --> 27:57.807
THEY WANT US OVER
AT THE NEXT BOMB SITE,

27:57.810 --> 27:59.943
PRIORITY ONE.
OKAY.

27:59.945 --> 28:01.045
WHAT?

28:01.046 --> 28:02.146
IT'S CLARK.
HE'S AT A MUNICIPAL BUILDING

28:02.148 --> 28:03.714
AND I HAVEN'T HEARD
FROM HIM.

28:03.716 --> 28:04.748
CITY HALL?
DONNA,
I DON'T KNOW.

28:04.750 --> 28:06.100
ED, I'M HEADED THERE.

28:06.101 --> 28:07.451
I'LL CALL YOU AS SOON
AS I CAN, OKAY?

28:07.453 --> 28:09.753
COME ON,
WHAT'RE THE ODDS, RIGHT?

28:09.755 --> 28:10.754
OKAY.

28:10.755 --> 28:11.754
I'LL CALL YOU
WHEN I GET THERE.

28:11.757 --> 28:13.323
NK YOU.
.
ALL RIGHT?

28:21.100 --> 28:23.133
SAM:
HOW'S THE LEG, JULES?

28:23.135 --> 28:24.134
DID YOU TALK
TO YOUR FOLKS?

28:24.136 --> 28:25.369
I CAN'T GET A HOLD
OF 'EM.

28:25.371 --> 28:26.403
I'M SURE THEY'RE FINE,
THOUGH.

28:26.405 --> 28:28.338
YEAH.
HOW ARE YOU?

28:29.408 --> 28:30.874
WE'RE GOOD.

28:34.747 --> 28:36.213
SO YOU STILL HAVEN'T HEARD
FROM HIM AT ALL?

28:36.215 --> 28:37.537
SOPHIE:
I HAVEN'T.

28:37.538 --> 28:38.860
IT'S NOT LIKE HIM,
NOT THIS LONG.

28:38.861 --> 28:40.183
ED:
WELL, YOU KNOW, SOPH,
LIKE I SAID, HE'S PROBABLY...

28:40.186 --> 28:42.019
PROBABLY JUST GOT
HIS HEADPHONES ON, SO...

28:42.020 --> 28:43.853
<i> SOPHIE:</i>
<i> ED, I'M WORRIED.</i>
<i> WHY HASN'T HE CALLED?</i>

28:43.856 --> 28:45.189
I MEAN,
WHAT IF SOMETHING HAPPENED?

28:45.191 --> 28:46.924
SOPH, WE'RE GONNA
GET HIM HOME OKAY.

28:46.926 --> 28:48.209
HE'S GONNA BE FINE.

28:48.210 --> 28:49.493
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> GUYS, CHECK YOUR INBOXES.</i>

28:49.495 --> 28:51.495
<i> ED:</i>
<i> SOPH, I GOTTA GO.</i>
<i> I LOVE YOU.</i>

28:51.497 --> 28:53.064
OKAY.
(PHONE BEEPS)

28:53.065 --> 28:54.632
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> 52 DIVISION JUST FORWARDED</i>
<i> AN EMAIL</i>

28:54.633 --> 28:56.200
FROM THE GUY CLAIMING
TO BE THE BOMBER.

28:56.202 --> 28:57.434
IT COMES WITH A TUBE LINK.

28:57.436 --> 28:59.369
CLAIMS TO BE HIS MANIFESTO.

28:59.371 --> 29:00.804
HE SENT A TUBE LINK
TO THE POLICE?

29:00.805 --> 29:02.238
SPIKE:
NO, TO THE MEDIA OUTLETS,
AND THEY SENT IT TO US.

29:02.241 --> 29:04.141
(CLICKS ON THE LINK)

29:04.142 --> 29:06.042
BOMBER:
I LIKE TO THINK OF MYSELF
AS A THOUGHT-PROVOKER,

29:06.045 --> 29:07.811
A PROVOCATEUR.

29:07.813 --> 29:09.563
<i> BUT TO PROVOKE THOUGHT,</i>

29:09.564 --> 29:11.314
<i> FIRST I NEED TO GET</i>
<i> YOUR FULL ATTENTION.</i>

29:11.317 --> 29:14.351
WE LIVE IN MEDIA-SATURATED,
TECHNOLOGY-FRACTURED,

29:14.353 --> 29:16.453
SHORT-ATTENTION-SPAN TIMES;

29:16.455 --> 29:18.789
IT'S NOT EASY TO SECURE
AN AUDIENCE.

29:18.791 --> 29:20.758
I HOPE
WHAT I SET IN MOTION TODAY

29:20.760 --> 29:22.226
HAS SUCCEEDED ON THAT FRONT.

29:22.228 --> 29:24.495
SPIKE:
THIS THING GOES ON
FOR 47 MINUTES.

29:24.497 --> 29:26.414
(SIREN WAILS NEARBY)

29:26.415 --> 29:28.332
JULES:
CAN YOU TRACK THE COMPUTER
HE POSTED THAT FROM?

29:28.334 --> 29:29.750
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i>NO; HE'S TRANSCODED THE VIDEO -</i>

29:29.751 --> 29:31.167
I CAN'T GET
TO THE ORIGINAL FILE,

29:31.170 --> 29:33.137
<i> AND IT LOOKS LIKE HE PUT IT UP</i>
<i> USING A DUMMY ACCOUNT.</i>

29:33.139 --> 29:34.304
IT'S TOTALLY ANONYMOUS.

29:34.306 --> 29:35.923
HOW DO YOU KNOW
IT WAS A DUMMY ACCOUNT?

29:35.924 --> 29:37.541
BECAUSE HE CALLED IT
DUMMY, UNDERSCORE, ACCOUNT.

29:37.543 --> 29:40.043
<i> SAM:</i>
<i> DID THE EMAIL ITSELF</i>
<i> COME FROM THE SAME COMPUTER?</i>

29:40.045 --> 29:41.478
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> WELL, HE'S BEEN SO CAREFUL</i>
<i> TO COVER HIS TRACKS,</i>

29:41.480 --> 29:42.780
I CAN'T SEE-
(COMPUTER BEEPS)

29:42.782 --> 29:44.381
HOLD ON A SECOND.

29:44.383 --> 29:46.133
<i> I THINK HE SLIPPED UP.</i>

29:46.134 --> 29:47.884
THIS PUBLICITY THING,
HE SENT IT FROM A SMART PHONE.

29:47.887 --> 29:49.286
I CAN BACK-TRACK THAT.

29:49.288 --> 29:50.854
<i> I CAN GET YOU A NUMBER.</i>

29:50.856 --> 29:53.357
<i> PHONE NUMBER IS 555-0193.</i>

29:54.293 --> 29:56.393
I MIGHT BE ABLE
TO GET A LOCATION TOO.

29:56.394 --> 29:58.494
(COMPUTER BEEPS)
NO. HE'S TURNED OFF THE GPS,
BUT WE CAN STILL GET A NAME.

29:58.497 --> 30:00.164
WINNIE?

30:00.165 --> 30:01.832
THE SMART PHONE IS REGISTERED
TO AN ANSON P. HOLT.

30:01.834 --> 30:03.500
I'M SENDING HIS ADDRESS
TO YOU NOW.

30:03.502 --> 30:04.501
ED! LET'S MOVE,
LET'S GO!

30:04.503 --> 30:05.792
JULES:
BOSS?

30:05.793 --> 30:07.082
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> YEAH, JULES,</i>
<i> YOU STAY OFF THAT LEG.</i>

30:07.083 --> 30:08.372
<i> I NEED YOUR HELP PROFILING.</i>

30:08.374 --> 30:09.840
<i> LET'S FIGURE OUT</i>
<i> WHO OUR "THOUGHT PROVOKER" IS,</i>

30:09.842 --> 30:11.542
MAYBE WE CAN FIGURE OUT
WHERE HIS BOMBS ARE.

30:11.544 --> 30:12.943
COPY.

30:12.945 --> 30:14.845
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> ED, I'M ON MY WAY!</i>

30:14.847 --> 30:16.547
BOSS, THESE BOMBS ARE
A HALF HOUR APART.

30:16.549 --> 30:17.881
IF HE'S STICKS
TO HIS PROMISE...

30:17.883 --> 30:19.583
PARKER:
I KNOW;

30:19.585 --> 30:21.385
ELEVEN MINUTES
TILL THE NEXT ONE BLOWS.

30:31.030 --> 30:33.163
(DOOR CRASHES OPEN)

30:39.038 --> 30:40.337
SPIKE: CLEAR!
ED: CLEAR!

30:40.339 --> 30:42.072
<i> SAM: CLEAR!</i>
<i> LEAH: CLEAR!</i>

30:42.074 --> 30:43.974
<i> ED:</i>
<i> GREG, HE'S NOT HERE.</i>

30:43.975 --> 30:45.875
<i> JULES:</i>
<i> BOSS, I THINK HE SEES THIS</i>
<i> AS TAKING A STAND</i>

30:45.878 --> 30:47.528
FOR PERSONAL FREEDOM;

30:47.529 --> 30:49.179
THE LIBERTY OF THE INDIVIDUAL
AGAINST CONTROL -

30:49.181 --> 30:50.581
<i> ANY KIND OF CONTROL.</i>

30:50.583 --> 30:52.115
HE WANTS TO SHOW WE CAN
ALL FIGHT BACK

30:52.117 --> 30:53.917
BY CLAIMING OUR OWN
PERSONAL AUTONOMY.

30:53.919 --> 30:55.619
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> CUT THE PUPPET STRINGS.</i>
<i> I GET IT, JULES,</i>

30:55.621 --> 30:58.088
BUT IT'S JUST GENERAL
THEORETICAL JUSTIFICATION.

30:58.090 --> 30:59.723
<i> JULES:</i>
<i> YEAH, BUT LOOK,</i>

30:59.724 --> 31:01.357
HE ACTUALLY LISTS THE FORCES
HE'S FIGHTING AGAINST.

31:01.360 --> 31:03.393
EACH ONE GETS A GRAPHIC.

31:03.395 --> 31:06.597
WHAT IF EACH ONE IS A TARGET
HE'S PLANNING ON HITTING?

31:06.599 --> 31:09.199
THE GOVERNMENT
FEDERAL BUILDING.

31:09.201 --> 31:12.369
BOMBER:
JUST LIKE A SECURITY BLANKET,
THE SAFETY IS ALL AN ILLUSION,

31:12.371 --> 31:14.071
<i> AND THE CHILD</i>
<i> THAT DEPENDS ON IT</i>

31:14.073 --> 31:16.106
<i> WILL SOON BE FORCED</i>
<i> TO GROW UP.</i>

31:16.108 --> 31:17.591
"COMMUNICATIONS" -

31:17.592 --> 31:19.075
THAT'S WHAT HE CALLS THE CITY'S
"SECURITY BLANKET."

31:19.078 --> 31:21.278
WELL, THAT'S 911 -
THE PEOPLE WHO KEEP US SAFE.

31:21.280 --> 31:23.013
JULES:
PETTY POLITICS?

31:23.015 --> 31:24.147
SPIKE:
CITY HALL.

31:24.149 --> 31:25.666
IT'S ALL LINING UP.

31:25.667 --> 31:27.184
SPIKE:
HOW MANY FORCES IS THIS GUY
FIGHTING AGAINST?

31:28.354 --> 31:31.021
<i> JULES:</i>
<i> SEVEN, EIGHT, NINE...</i>

31:31.023 --> 31:32.956
WE GOT TEN TARGETS.

31:32.958 --> 31:35.292
OKAY, WE'RE ONTO THIS BASTARD.
GOOD WORK, JULES.

31:35.294 --> 31:37.027
PARKER:
BUT THAT DOESN'T TELL US
WHERE THE BOMBS ARE.

31:37.029 --> 31:38.395
<i> "JUSTICE" CAN MEAN</i>
<i> ANY COURTHOUSE. </i>

31:38.397 --> 31:41.265
<i> "MEDIA" COULD MEAN</i>
<i> ANY TELEVISION STATION.</i>

31:41.267 --> 31:43.333
ANSON HOLT
IS A PSYCHOLOGIST.

31:43.335 --> 31:44.980
GO HEAD, WINNIE.

31:44.981 --> 31:46.626
<i> WINNIE:</i>
<i> HE'S A PROFESSOR</i>
<i> AT BROOKFIELD UNIVERSITY.</i>

31:46.627 --> 31:48.272
<i> LOTS OF PUBLICATIONS,</i>
<i> MAJOR RESEARCH GRANTS,</i>

31:48.274 --> 31:49.757
LECTURE TOURS...

31:49.758 --> 31:51.241
AND ONE OF THE HIGHEST
STUDENT RATINGS OF THE FACULTY.

31:51.243 --> 31:52.643
<i> (COMPUTER BEEPS)</i>
<i> OH! CORRECTION.</i>

31:52.645 --> 31:54.278
HE WAS "LET GO"
FROM THE UNIVERSITY

31:54.280 --> 31:55.279
FIVE YEARS AGO.

31:55.281 --> 31:56.692
WHY?

31:56.693 --> 31:58.104
WINNIE:
NO REASON ANYONE WAS WILLING
TO PUT ON THE RECORD.

31:58.105 --> 31:59.516
ALL RIGHT, GET ME THE HEAD
OF THE PSYCHOLOGY DEPARTMENT,

31:59.518 --> 32:00.951
AND I'LL GET IT
OUT OF THEM.

32:00.952 --> 32:02.385
WINNIE:
DAY LIKE TODAY, BOSS,
I'M GONNA DO MY BEST, BUT-

32:02.388 --> 32:04.521
(SNAPS)
WINNIE, JUST FIND THEM.

32:04.523 --> 32:06.223
SORRY, BOSS,
WILL DO.

32:07.159 --> 32:08.926
(ED'S PHONE RINGS)

32:13.098 --> 32:15.165
WHERE THE HELL ARE YOU?

32:15.167 --> 32:16.566
<i> CLARK:</i>
<i> (GASPS) DAD...</i>

32:16.568 --> 32:18.669
CLARK, WHAT'S GOING ON?
TALK TO ME!

32:18.671 --> 32:20.638
TALK TO ME.

32:20.639 --> 32:22.606
<i> CLARK:</i>
<i> (GASPS IN PAIN)</i>
<i> CAN'T MOVE.</i>

32:22.608 --> 32:23.674
CLARK?

32:25.678 --> 32:28.278
CLARK,
YOU'RE AT CITY HALL?

32:28.280 --> 32:29.646
<i> (CLARK GROANS)</i>

32:29.648 --> 32:32.215
(VOICE HITCHES)
ARE YOU IN CITY HALL?

32:32.217 --> 32:34.051
CLARK:
(GROANS) YES...

32:34.053 --> 32:35.252
<i> RUSH!</i>

32:35.254 --> 32:36.586
OKAY, OKAY,
STAY WITH ME.

32:36.588 --> 32:38.221
CLARK:
CAN'T... (GRUNTS)

32:38.223 --> 32:40.324
<i> ED:</i>
<i> IT'S OKAY,</i>
<i> JUST STAY WITH ME.</i>

32:40.326 --> 32:41.992
<i> CLARK:</i>
<i> (GROANING) I'M HERE.</i>

32:41.993 --> 32:43.659
ED:
CALL DONNA,
TELL HER CLARK'S AT CITY HALL.

32:43.662 --> 32:45.128
TRACK HIS PHONE.

32:46.065 --> 32:47.698
I'M COMING TO GET YOU,
STAY WITH ME.

32:47.700 --> 32:49.700
SPIKE:
BOSS, YOU COPY THAT?

32:49.702 --> 32:51.301
YEAH, I DID, SPIKE.

32:54.373 --> 32:56.707
BOSS, THERE WAS A FALSE BACK
ON HIS OFFICE BOOKSHELF.

32:56.709 --> 32:58.175
WHAT WAS HE HIDING?

32:58.177 --> 32:59.727
SAM:
SOME PRETTY DISTURBING BOOKS.

32:59.728 --> 33:01.278
"EMBRACING SADISM."
"THE COURAGE TO DOMINATE."

33:01.280 --> 33:02.679
HE'S GOT A PRIVATE
DVD COLLECTION,

33:02.681 --> 33:04.147
PLAIN COVERS.

33:04.148 --> 33:05.614
JULES:
HEY, GUYS, I THINK I FOUND
ANOTHER TARGET.

33:05.617 --> 33:07.317
<i> HE'S HIT COMMUNICATIONS,</i>
<i> BIG GOVERNMENT,</i>

33:07.319 --> 33:08.618
<i> PETTY POLITICS.</i>

33:08.620 --> 33:10.554
BUT HIS BIGGEST GRUDGE TO DATE
IS EDUCATION.

33:10.556 --> 33:12.422
LISTEN TO THIS.

33:12.424 --> 33:15.392
BOMBER:
SUBSTITUTE "INSTITUTION
OF HIGHER LEARNING"

33:15.394 --> 33:17.694
FOR "INSTITUTION OF CONFORMING
AND CRUSHING."

33:17.696 --> 33:19.596
I WILL CRUSH YOU BACK.

33:19.598 --> 33:22.733
CRUSH YOU WHERE IT BEGAN
IN THAT LAB.

33:22.735 --> 33:24.735
I WILL BE WATCHING YOU.

33:24.737 --> 33:26.303
PARKER:
HIS OLD WORKPLACE,
WHERE HIS GRUDGE BEGAN.

33:26.305 --> 33:28.105
WE NEED TO FIND THAT LAB.

33:28.107 --> 33:30.307
(SIREN WAILS, HORN BLASTS,
TIRES SQUEAL)

33:30.309 --> 33:33.343
CLARK, LET ME ASK YOU,
DO YOU FEEL ANY PAIN?

33:33.345 --> 33:37.247
CLARK:
(GROANING) YEAH, MY SIDE...
IT HURTS.

33:37.249 --> 33:39.182
LEGS...
LEGS ARE KILLING.

33:39.184 --> 33:41.218
ED:
PAIN'S GOOD, BUDDY.
IT MEANS YOUR SPINE'S OKAY.

33:41.220 --> 33:42.686
(HONKING) NOW, CLARK,
I KNOW THIS HARD,

33:42.688 --> 33:44.221
BUT I NEED YOU
TO JUST SLOW YOUR BREATHING

33:44.223 --> 33:46.156
RIGHT DOWN FOR ME.

33:46.158 --> 33:48.058
<i>LET'S GET THAT HEART RATE DOWN,</i>
<i> OKAY?</i>

33:48.060 --> 33:49.793
<i> IT'LL HELP YOU THINK</i>
<i> STRAIGHT,</i>

33:49.794 --> 33:51.527
<i> YOU'RE NOT GONNA LOSE</i>
<i> SO MUCH BLOOD.</i>

33:51.528 --> 33:53.261
I TAUGHT YOU SNIPER BREATHING,
RIGHT, CLARK?

33:53.265 --> 33:54.331
(NO RESPONSE)

33:55.367 --> 33:57.200
CLARK?

33:57.202 --> 33:58.301
(LABOURED BREATHS)

33:58.303 --> 33:59.503
<i> CLARK!</i>

34:00.439 --> 34:02.339
<i> I KNOW IT'S HARD FOR YOU</i>
<i> TO SPEAK, BUT...</i>

34:02.341 --> 34:04.508
CLARK,
I KNOW YOU CAN HEAR ME.

34:04.510 --> 34:07.511
YOU ARE SUCH A STRONG KID
AND I AM SO PROUD OF YOU.

34:07.513 --> 34:10.047
<i> NOW, I NEED YOU</i>
<i> TO STAY STRONG.</i>

34:10.049 --> 34:11.381
<i> I'M ON MY WAY.</i>

34:11.383 --> 34:14.251
(FIGHTING TEARS)
I LOVE YOU, BUDDY.
I LOVE YOU.

34:16.288 --> 34:18.321
WINNIE:
SARGE, I TRACKED DOWN
THE DEAN OF PSYCHOLOGY,

34:18.323 --> 34:19.389
MONICA BUTLER.

34:19.390 --> 34:20.456
PARKER:
THAT'S FANTASTIC, WINNIE!

34:20.459 --> 34:21.525
(HORNS BLAST)

34:23.829 --> 34:25.228
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> PROFESSOR BUTLER?</i>

34:25.230 --> 34:26.830
MY NAME IS
SERGEANT GREG PARKER.

34:26.831 --> 34:28.431
I'M WITH THE POLICE
STRATEGIC RESPONSE UNIT.

34:28.434 --> 34:30.100
I NEED YOU TO ANSWER
A FEW QUESTIONS.

34:30.102 --> 34:31.268
UH, YES, OF COURSE.

34:31.269 --> 34:32.435
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> WHERE'S THE LAB</i>
<i> ANSON HOLT WORKED</i>

34:32.438 --> 34:34.337
BEFORE HE WAS FIRED?

34:34.339 --> 34:36.406
UH, THAT WAS THE OLD
CASEY JEFFERS BUILDING,

34:36.408 --> 34:38.508
BUT THAT'S NOT IN USE ANY MORE.
WHY?

34:38.510 --> 34:39.810
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> OKAY, JUST HOLD ON THE LINE.</i>

34:39.812 --> 34:42.279
WINNIE? I WANT A CITYWIDE SEARCH
FOR ANSON HOLT.

34:42.281 --> 34:44.681
<i> ANYONE WHO'S NOT AT A BOMBSITE</i>
<i> IS LOOKING FOR THIS BASTARD.</i>

34:44.683 --> 34:46.783
AND WHICH TEAM IS CLOSEST
TO THE CASEY JEFFERS BUILDING

34:46.785 --> 34:48.251
RIGHT NOW?

34:48.253 --> 34:49.453
DONNA. TEAM THREE.

34:49.455 --> 34:50.854
PARKER:
GREAT. DONNA, YOU HEAR ME?

34:50.855 --> 34:52.254
DONNA:
YEAH, BOSS.
(CALLING OUT) CLARK!

34:52.257 --> 34:53.657
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> DONNA, I NEED YOU</i>
<i> TO GET TO THAT LAB.</i>

34:53.659 --> 34:55.358
THERE COULD BE
ANOTHER BOMB THERE.

34:55.360 --> 34:57.160
DONNA:
I'M AT CITY HALL
LOOKING FOR CLARK.

34:57.162 --> 34:58.879
(CALLING OUT)
ANYBODY HEAR ME?

34:58.880 --> 35:00.597
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> DONNA, YOU'RE THE CLOSEST TEAM</i>
<i> TO THAT SITE, ALL RIGHT?</i>

35:00.599 --> 35:02.165
I'LL BE RIGHT BEHIND YOU.

35:02.166 --> 35:03.732
DONNA:
I KNOW PROTOCOL, BOSS,
BUT THIS IS ED'S KID.

35:03.735 --> 35:06.236
ED:
DONNA, I'M ALMOST THERE.
YOU GOTTA GO.

35:06.238 --> 35:07.771
GET TO THE LAB -
PRIORITY OF LIFE.

35:07.773 --> 35:10.373
DONNA:
(CALLING OUT)
CLARK! EDDIE, I'M RIGHT HERE!

35:10.375 --> 35:12.442
DONNA, I GOT IT.

35:12.444 --> 35:13.577
DONNA:
(CALLING OUT)
CLARK?

35:13.579 --> 35:15.545
DONNA, THANK YOU
FOR EVERYTHING.

35:15.547 --> 35:16.880
DONNA:
JIMMY, WE GOTTA GO.

35:16.882 --> 35:18.148
TEAM THREE,
LET'S MOVE!

35:18.150 --> 35:19.416
DONNA, STAY SAFE.

35:19.418 --> 35:21.418
DONNA:
ALWAYS, EDDIE.

35:26.125 --> 35:29.726
PARKER:
EVERYONE,
YOU ARE THE HEART AND SOUL.

35:32.297 --> 35:34.197
ALL OF YOU,
THANK YOU.

35:37.703 --> 35:39.436
(SIRENS WAIL)

35:39.438 --> 35:42.439
SOPH, WE KNOW WHERE HE IS.

35:42.441 --> 35:44.174
<i> BUT LISTEN TO ME...</i>

35:44.176 --> 35:46.743
SOPHIE, HE'S HURT.
HE'S IN ONE OF THE BUILDINGS.

35:46.745 --> 35:49.646
OH, ED...

35:49.647 --> 35:52.548
<i> ED:</i>
<i> LOOK, I KNOW YOU'RE SCARED</i>
<i> AND I'M SCARED TOO,</i>

35:52.551 --> 35:54.351
BUT HE'S TOUGH.

35:54.353 --> 35:55.552
SOPHIE: (SOBBING)
<i> ED: SOPH, HE'S TOU-</i>

35:55.554 --> 35:56.653
<i> (PHONE BEEPS)</i>
<i> HOLD ON, HOLD ON, SOPH.</i>

35:56.655 --> 35:59.489
I GOT EMS.
HOLD ON, PLEASE.

35:59.491 --> 36:00.624
STEVE.

36:00.626 --> 36:02.042
STEVE:
ED, WE TRACKED HIS CELL SIGNAL

36:02.043 --> 36:03.459
TO THE SECOND LEVEL
OF THE PARKING GARAGE,

36:03.462 --> 36:05.862
BUT WE HAVEN'T FOUND HIM YET.

36:06.798 --> 36:09.933
<i> HOLD ON! ED! ED!</i>
<i> I GOT THE CAR.</i>

36:09.935 --> 36:11.668
I'M SORRY, ED,
BUT UH...

36:11.670 --> 36:13.570
<i> IT'S CRUSHED UNDER CONCRETE.</i>

36:13.572 --> 36:15.172
IT'S NOT LOOKING GOOD.

36:15.174 --> 36:16.706
OKAY, I'M RIGHT THERE.

36:16.708 --> 36:18.175
SOPH?

36:18.177 --> 36:19.543
NOW, I'M GONNA
GET HIM OUT.

36:19.545 --> 36:21.211
NOW YOU GOTTA BELIEVE THAT,
'KAY?

36:21.213 --> 36:22.879
<i> I'M GONNA BRING HIM HOME,</i>
<i> OKAY, BABY?</i>

36:22.881 --> 36:24.681
(SOBBING, DEVASTATED)

36:37.329 --> 36:38.628
<i> DONNA: </i>
<i> GUYS...</i>

36:38.630 --> 36:40.764
I THINK I'VE GOT A POSITIVE ID
ON ANSON HOLT.

36:40.766 --> 36:42.532
<i> HE'S HERE AT THE LAB.</i>

36:42.534 --> 36:43.567
(SIREN WAILS)

36:43.569 --> 36:44.768
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> ALL RIGHT, DONNA,</i>

36:44.769 --> 36:45.968
THERE ARE BOMBS TICKING DOWN
ALL ACROSS THIS CITY;

36:45.971 --> 36:47.437
<i> NO TIME FOR KID GLOVES.</i>

36:47.439 --> 36:49.506
DONNA:
COPY. GO.

36:50.542 --> 36:52.375
ANSON HOLT, PUT YOUR HANDS
WHERE I CAN SEE THEM!

36:52.377 --> 36:54.778
TEAM THREE:
SRU! ON THE GROUND!
POLICE! GET DOWN NOW!

36:54.780 --> 36:57.380
GET DOWN ON THE GROUND
RIGHT NOW!

36:57.382 --> 36:58.615
GET ON THE GROUND!

36:59.551 --> 37:00.684
DONNA:
TURN HIM.

37:01.887 --> 37:03.887
<i> WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.</i>

37:13.432 --> 37:15.232
DONNA:
YOU MAKE ONE MOVE
I DON'T TELL YOU TO MAKE,

37:15.234 --> 37:16.399
YOU GET SHOT,

37:16.401 --> 37:17.767
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?

37:19.471 --> 37:20.704
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?!

37:21.640 --> 37:23.218
GOOD!

37:23.219 --> 37:24.797
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> DONNA, WHAT'S GOING ON?</i>

37:24.798 --> 37:26.376
DONNA:
HE'S STRAPPED TO AN M112
DEMOLITION CHARGE,

37:26.378 --> 37:27.510
AND HE'S WATCHING
THE WHOLE CITY CARNAGE

37:27.512 --> 37:28.912
ON HIS COMPUTER SCREENS.

37:28.914 --> 37:30.547
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> DONNA, I'M RIGHT BEHIND YOU.</i>

37:30.549 --> 37:33.283
PROFESSOR BUTLER,
WHY DID ANSON HOLT GET FIRED?

37:34.519 --> 37:36.653
ETHICAL ISSUES WERE
BROUGHT TO OUR ATTENTION.

37:36.655 --> 37:38.288
LISTEN TO ME, PROFESSOR,
IN UNDER TWO MINUTES,

37:38.290 --> 37:39.990
I'M GONNA TRY TO TALK THIS MAN
OUT OF BLOWING UP

37:39.992 --> 37:42.459
MORE INNOCENT CIVILIANS.

37:42.461 --> 37:44.661
<i> PLEASE JUST TELL ME</i>
<i> WHAT HAPPENED IN THAT LAB.</i>

37:44.663 --> 37:46.596
HE WAS FIRED
BECAUSE OF A SERIES

37:46.598 --> 37:48.465
OF PSYCHOLOGICALLY ABUSIVE
EXPERIMENTS

37:48.467 --> 37:51.501
THAT HE PERFORMED THERE
ON STUDENT VOLUNTEERS.

37:51.503 --> 37:52.969
HE WAS A SADIST?

37:52.971 --> 37:54.037
YES.

37:56.942 --> 37:58.642
ONE WOMAN DOWNRANGE,
THE REST OF YOU GO.

37:58.644 --> 37:59.632
JIMMY:
SOMEBODY'S GOTTA COVER HIM.

37:59.633 --> 38:00.621
IF HE MAKES A PLAY
WHEN YOU'RE WORKING...

38:00.622 --> 38:01.610
DONNA:
OKAY, OKAY.
JIMMY, STAY.

38:01.613 --> 38:03.480
THE REST OF YOU GO.

38:05.684 --> 38:07.851
YOU'RE GONNA RAISE YOUR ARMS,
VERY SLOWLY,

38:07.853 --> 38:10.854
AWAY FROM YOUR BODY,
INTO THE AIR.

38:10.856 --> 38:11.921
DO IT.

38:17.896 --> 38:19.863
YOU'RE GONNA TALK TO ME,
HOLT.

38:19.865 --> 38:23.600
YOU TELL ME WHERE
THE REST OF THE BOMBS ARE!

38:25.771 --> 38:27.537
WINNIE!

38:27.539 --> 38:28.605
WINNIE:
ARE YOU OKAY?

38:28.607 --> 38:29.606
YEAH, WE'RE FINE.

38:29.608 --> 38:30.640
OKAY.
(TYPES FURIOUSLY)

38:30.642 --> 38:32.642
<i> ED:</i>
<i> STEVE! STEVE!</i>

38:33.779 --> 38:36.163
STEVE: ED!
ED: WHERE IS HE?

38:36.164 --> 38:38.548
STEVE:
THE PHONE SIGNAL'S HERE, MAN.
IT'S GOTTA BE HIM.

38:38.550 --> 38:40.016
CLARK!

38:40.018 --> 38:41.084
<i> CLARK!</i>

38:43.021 --> 38:44.888
(STARTS SHIFTING DEBRIS)

38:45.824 --> 38:46.890
CLARK!

38:53.365 --> 38:56.900
DONNA:
SPIKE, I GOT NO TIMER.
I GOT C4 AND WIRES.

38:57.836 --> 38:59.602
THIS DOESN'T LOOK LIKE
YOUR 911 BOMB.

38:59.604 --> 39:01.004
DONNA, IF THERE'S NO TIMER
ON THE BOMB,

39:01.005 --> 39:02.405
THEN YOU CAN WAIT
TILL I GET THERE.

39:02.407 --> 39:04.007
<i> DONNA:</i>
<i> NO! I CAN HANDLE IT.</i>

39:06.645 --> 39:08.678
HOW MANY WIRES DO YOU SEE?

39:08.680 --> 39:11.414
DONNA:
UH... (COUNTING TO HERSELF)

39:12.684 --> 39:14.117
EIGHTEEN.

39:14.119 --> 39:15.469
JIMMY:
ARMS UP!

39:15.470 --> 39:16.820
OKAY, THE BOMB'S EXPOSED,
THAT'S GOOD.

39:16.822 --> 39:19.689
<i> NOW, JUST FIND THE DETONATOR.</i>

39:19.691 --> 39:21.458
DONNA:
I DON'T SEE ANY DETONATOR.

39:21.460 --> 39:22.692
SPIKE:
NO, THERE'S GOTTA BE
A DETONATOR.

39:22.694 --> 39:24.060
DONNA:
I DON'T SEE IT,
I'M LOOKING.

39:24.062 --> 39:25.061
IS THIS THE FASTEST WAY?

39:25.063 --> 39:26.346
SAM:
IT'S THE ONLY WAY.

39:26.347 --> 39:27.630
EVERY ON RAMP AND HIGHWAY
IS JAMMED RIGHT NOW.

39:27.632 --> 39:29.132
WE'RE GOING AS FAST
AS WE CAN.

39:29.134 --> 39:31.000
<i> JULES:</i>
<i> DONNA, HOW'S OUR SUBJECT?</i>

39:31.002 --> 39:33.470
DONNA:
QUIET, CO-OPERATIVE -
COULD BE THE GUN ON HIS HEAD.

39:33.472 --> 39:34.738
<i> JULES:</i>
<i> BOSS, THIS MAKE ANY SENSE</i>
<i> TO YOU?</i>

39:34.740 --> 39:35.939
IF HE WAS GONNA BLOW
HIMSELF UP,

39:35.941 --> 39:37.674
WHY DIDN'T HE ALREADY DO IT?

39:38.643 --> 39:40.977
DONNA:
THIS IS YOUR VERY LAST CHANCE.

39:40.979 --> 39:44.147
TELL ME WHERE THE DETONATOR IS
RIGHT NOW!

39:44.149 --> 39:46.983
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

39:46.985 --> 39:48.985
WHAT'RE YOU LOOKING AT?

